187  struct IMutableContext : IContext
188  {
189  virtual ~IMutableContext();
190  virtual void setResultCapture( IResultCapture* resultCapture ) = 0;
191  virtual void setRunner( IRunner* runner ) = 0;
192  virtual void setConfig( IConfig const* config ) = 0;
193 
194  private:
195  static IMutableContext *currentContext;
196  friend IMutableContext& getCurrentMutableContext();
197  friend void cleanUpContext();
198  static void createContext();
199  };
200 
201  inline IMutableContext& getCurrentMutableContext()
202  {
203  if( !IMutableContext::currentContext )
204  IMutableContext::createContext();
205  // NOLINTNEXTLINE(clang-analyzer-core.uninitialized.UndefReturn)
206  return *IMutableContext::currentContext;
207  }
208 
209  inline IContext& getCurrentContext()
210  {
211  return getCurrentMutableContext();
212  }

238 #ifndef CATCH_COMPILER_CAPABILITIES_HPP_INCLUDED

241 // Detect a number of compiler features - by compiler
242 // The following features are defined:
243 //
244 // CATCH_CONFIG_COUNTER : is the __COUNTER__ macro supported?
245 // CATCH_CONFIG_WINDOWS_SEH : is Windows SEH supported?
246 // CATCH_CONFIG_POSIX_SIGNALS : are POSIX signals supported?
247 // CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS : Are exceptions enabled?
248 // ****************
249 // Note to maintainers: if new toggles are added please document them
250 // in configuration.md, too
251 // ****************
252 
253 // In general each macro has a _NO_<feature name> form
254 // (e.g. CATCH_CONFIG_NO_POSIX_SIGNALS) which disables the feature.
255 // Many features, at point of detection, define an _INTERNAL_ macro, so they
256 // can be combined, en-mass, with the _NO_ forms later.
257 
258 
259

261 #define CATCH_PLATFORM_HPP_INCLUDED

264 # include <TargetConditionals.h>
265 # if TARGET_OS_OSX == 1
266 # define CATCH_PLATFORM_MAC
267 # elif TARGET_OS_IPHONE == 1
268 # define CATCH_PLATFORM_IPHONE
269 # endif
270 
271 #elif defined(linux) || defined(__linux) || defined(__linux__)
272 # define CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX
273 
274 #elif defined(WIN32) || defined(__WIN32__) || defined(_WIN32) || defined(_MSC_VER) || defined(__MINGW32__)
275 # define CATCH_PLATFORM_WINDOWS
276 #endif
277 
278 #endif // CATCH_PLATFORM_HPP_INCLUDED

292 // We have to avoid both ICC and Clang, because they try to mask themselves
293 // as gcc, and we want only GCC in this block
294 #if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && !defined(__ICC) && !defined(__CUDACC__)
295 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic push" )
296 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic pop" )
297 
298 // This only works on GCC 9+. so we have to also add a global suppression of Wparentheses
299 // for older versions of GCC.
300 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
301  _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )
302 
303 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
304  _Pragma( "GCC diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-variable\"" )
305 
306 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(...) (void)__builtin_constant_p(__VA_ARGS__)
307 
308 #endif
309 
310 #if defined(__clang__)
311 
312 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic push" )
313 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION _Pragma( "clang diagnostic pop" )
314 
315 // As of this writing, IBM XL's implementation of __builtin_constant_p has a bug
316 // which results in calls to destructors being emitted for each temporary,
317 // without a matching initialization. In practice, this can result in something
318 // like `std::string::~string` being called on an uninitialized value.
319 //
320 // For example, this code will likely segfault under IBM XL:
321 // ```
322 // REQUIRE(std::string("12") + "34" == "1234")
323 // ```
324 //
325 // Therefore, `CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN` is not implemented.
326 # if !defined(__ibmxl__) && !defined(__CUDACC__)
327 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(...) (void)__builtin_constant_p(__VA_ARGS__) /* NOLINT(cppcoreguidelines-pro-type-vararg, hicpp-vararg) */
328 # endif
329 
330 
331 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
332  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wexit-time-destructors\"" ) \
333  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wglobal-constructors\"")
334 
335 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
336  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wparentheses\"" )
337 
338 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_VARIABLE_WARNINGS \
339  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-variable\"" )
340 
341 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \
342  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wgnu-zero-variadic-macro-arguments\"" )
343 
344 # define CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_UNUSED_TEMPLATE_WARNINGS \
345  _Pragma( "clang diagnostic ignored \"-Wunused-template\"" )
346 
347 #endif // __clang__

637 #define CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED

639 #include <cstddef>
640 #include <string>
641 #include <iosfwd>
642 #include <cassert>
643 
644 namespace Catch {
645 
649  class StringRef {
650  public:
651  using size_type = std::size_t;
652  using const_iterator = const char*;
653 
654  private:
655  static constexpr char const* const s_empty = "";
656 
657  char const* m_start = s_empty;
658  size_type m_size = 0;
659 
660  public: // construction
661  constexpr StringRef() noexcept = default;
662 
663  StringRef( char const* rawChars ) noexcept;
664 
665  constexpr StringRef( char const* rawChars, size_type size ) noexcept
666  : m_start( rawChars ),
667  m_size( size )
668  {}
669 
670  StringRef( std::string const& stdString ) noexcept
671  : m_start( stdString.c_str() ),
672  m_size( stdString.size() )
673  {}
674 
675  explicit operator std::string() const {
676  return std::string(m_start, m_size);
677  }
678 
679  public: // operators
680  auto operator == ( StringRef const& other ) const noexcept -> bool;
681  auto operator != (StringRef const& other) const noexcept -> bool {
682  return !(*this == other);
683  }
684 
685  constexpr auto operator[] ( size_type index ) const noexcept -> char {
686  assert(index < m_size);
687  return m_start[index];
688  }
689 
690  bool operator<(StringRef const& rhs) const noexcept;
691 
692  public: // named queries
693  constexpr auto empty() const noexcept -> bool {
694  return m_size == 0;
695  }
696  constexpr auto size() const noexcept -> size_type {
697  return m_size;
698  }
699 
700  // Returns the current start pointer. If the StringRef is not
701  // null-terminated, throws std::domain_exception
702  auto c_str() const -> char const*;
703 
704  public: // substrings and searches
705  // Returns a substring of [start, start + length).
706  // If start + length > size(), then the substring is [start, start + size()).
707  // If start > size(), then the substring is empty.
708  constexpr StringRef substr(size_type start, size_type length) const noexcept {
709  if (start < m_size) {
710  const auto shortened_size = m_size - start;
711  return StringRef(m_start + start, (shortened_size < length) ? shortened_size : length);
712  } else {
713  return StringRef();
714  }
715  }
716 
717  // Returns the current start pointer. May not be null-terminated.
718  constexpr char const* data() const noexcept {
719  return m_start;
720  }
721 
722  constexpr auto isNullTerminated() const noexcept -> bool {
723  return m_start[m_size] == '\0';
724  }
725 
726  public: // iterators
727  constexpr const_iterator begin() const { return m_start; }
728  constexpr const_iterator end() const { return m_start + m_size; }
729 
730 
731  friend std::string& operator += (std::string& lhs, StringRef const& sr);
732  friend std::ostream& operator << (std::ostream& os, StringRef const& sr);
733  friend std::string operator+(StringRef lhs, StringRef rhs);
734  };
735 
736 
737  constexpr auto operator "" _sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> StringRef {
738  return StringRef( rawChars, size );
739  }
740 } // namespace Catch
741 
742 constexpr auto operator "" _catch_sr( char const* rawChars, std::size_t size ) noexcept -> Catch::StringRef {
743  return Catch::StringRef( rawChars, size );
744 }
745 
746 #endif // CATCH_STRINGREF_HPP_INCLUDED

889  // ResultWas::OfType enum
890  struct ResultWas { enum OfType {
891  Unknown = -1,
892  Ok = 0,
893  Info = 1,
894  Warning = 2,
895 
896  FailureBit = 0x10,
897 
898  ExpressionFailed = FailureBit | 1,
899  ExplicitFailure = FailureBit | 2,
900 
901  Exception = 0x100 | FailureBit,
902 
903  ThrewException = Exception | 1,
904  DidntThrowException = Exception | 2,
905 
906  FatalErrorCondition = 0x200 | FailureBit
907 
908  }; };

913 
914  // ResultDisposition::Flags enum
915  struct ResultDisposition { enum Flags {
916  Normal = 0x01,
917 
918  ContinueOnFailure = 0x02, // Failures fail test, but execution continues
919  FalseTest = 0x04, // Prefix expression with !
920  SuppressFail = 0x08 // Failures are reported but do not fail the test
921  }; };
922 
923  ResultDisposition::Flags operator | ( ResultDisposition::Flags lhs, ResultDisposition::Flags rhs );
924 
925  bool shouldContinueOnFailure( int flags );
926  inline bool isFalseTest( int flags ) { return ( flags & ResultDisposition::FalseTest ) != 0; }
927  bool shouldSuppressFailure( int flags );

1150 #ifndef CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
1151 #define CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED
1152 
1153 #include <cassert>
1154 #include <type_traits>
1155 
1156 namespace Catch {
1157 namespace Detail {
1158  // reimplementation of unique_ptr for improved compilation times
1159  // Does not support custom deleters (and thus does not require EBO)
1160  // Does not support arrays
1161  template <typename T>
1162  class unique_ptr {
1163  T* m_ptr;
1164  public:
1165  constexpr unique_ptr(std::nullptr_t = nullptr):
1166  m_ptr{}
1167  {}
1168  explicit constexpr unique_ptr(T* ptr):
1169  m_ptr(ptr)
1170  {}
1171 
1172  template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
1173  unique_ptr(unique_ptr<U>&& from):
1174  m_ptr(from.release())
1175  {}
1176 
1177  template <typename U, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_base_of<T, U>::value>>
1178  unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr<U>&& from) {
1179  reset(from.release());
1180 
1181  return *this;
1182  }
1183 
1184  unique_ptr(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
1185  unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr const&) = delete;
1186 
1187  unique_ptr(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept:
1188  m_ptr(rhs.m_ptr) {
1189  rhs.m_ptr = nullptr;
1190  }
1191  unique_ptr& operator=(unique_ptr&& rhs) noexcept {
1192  reset(rhs.release());
1193 
1194  return *this;
1195  }
1196 
1197  ~unique_ptr() {
1198  delete m_ptr;
1199  }
1200 
1201  T& operator*() {
1202  assert(m_ptr);
1203  return *m_ptr;
1204  }
1205  T const& operator*() const {
1206  assert(m_ptr);
1207  return *m_ptr;
1208  }
1209  T* operator->() const noexcept {
1210  assert(m_ptr);
1211  return m_ptr;
1212  }
1213 
1214  T* get() { return m_ptr; }
1215  T const* get() const { return m_ptr; }
1216 
1217  void reset(T* ptr = nullptr) {
1218  delete m_ptr;
1219  m_ptr = ptr;
1220  }
1221 
1222  T* release() {
1223  auto temp = m_ptr;
1224  m_ptr = nullptr;
1225  return temp;
1226  }
1227 
1228  explicit operator bool() const {
1229  return m_ptr;
1230  }
1231 
1232  friend void swap(unique_ptr& lhs, unique_ptr& rhs) {
1233  auto temp = lhs.m_ptr;
1234  lhs.m_ptr = rhs.m_ptr;
1235  rhs.m_ptr = temp;
1236  }
1237  };
1238 
1239  // Purposefully doesn't exist
1240  // We could also rely on compiler warning + werror for calling plain delete
1241  // on a T[], but this seems better.
1242  // Maybe add definition and a static assert?
1243  template <typename T>
1244  class unique_ptr<T[]>;
1245 
1246  template <typename T, typename... Args>
1247  unique_ptr<T> make_unique(Args&&... args) {
1248  // static_cast<Args&&> does the same thing as std::forward in
1249  // this case, but does not require including big header (<utility>)
1250  // and compiles faster thanks to not requiring template instantiation
1251  // and overload resolution
1252  return unique_ptr<T>(new T(static_cast<Args&&>(args)...));
1253  }
1254 
1255 
1256 } // end namespace Detail
1257 } // end namespace Catch
1258 
1259 #endif // CATCH_UNIQUE_PTR_HPP_INCLUDED

1270  template <typename Duration>
1271  struct Estimate {
1272  Duration point;
1273  Duration lower_bound;
1274  Duration upper_bound;
1275  double confidence_interval;
1276 
1277  template <typename Duration2>
1278  operator Estimate<Duration2>() const {
1279  return { point, lower_bound, upper_bound, confidence_interval };
1280  }
1281  };

1291 #define CATCH_OUTLIER_CLASSIFICATION_HPP_INCLUDED
1292 
1293 namespace Catch {
1294  namespace Benchmark {
1295  struct OutlierClassification {
1296  int samples_seen = 0;
1297  int low_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR below Q1
1298  int low_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR below Q1
1299  int high_mild = 0; // 1.5 to 3 times IQR above Q3
1300  int high_severe = 0; // more than 3 times IQR above Q3
1301 
1302  int total() const {
1303  return low_severe + low_mild + high_mild + high_severe;
1304  }
1305  };
1306  } // namespace Benchmark
1307 } // namespace Catch

1424  template <class Duration>

1428  std::vector<Duration> samples;
1429  Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> mean;
1430  Benchmark::Estimate<Duration> standardDeviation;
1431  Benchmark::OutlierClassification outliers;
1432  double outlierVariance;
1433 
1434  template <typename Duration2>
1435  explicit operator BenchmarkStats<Duration2>() const {
1436  std::vector<Duration2> samples2;
1437  samples2.reserve(samples.size());
1438  for (auto const& sample : samples) {
1439  samples2.push_back(Duration2(sample));
1440  }
1441  return {
1442  info,
1443  std::move(samples2),
1444  mean,
1445  standardDeviation,
1446  outliers,
1447  outlierVariance,
1448  };
1449  }

1568 #ifndef CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED
1569 #define CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED
1570 
1571 #if defined(_MSC_VER)
1572 # include <atomic> // atomic_thread_fence
1573 #endif
1574 
1575 #include <type_traits>
1576 #include <utility>
1577 
1578 namespace Catch {
1579  namespace Benchmark {
1580 #if defined(__GNUC__) || defined(__clang__)
1581  template <typename T>
1582  inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1583  asm volatile("" : : "g"(p) : "memory");
1584  }
1585  inline void keep_memory() {
1586  asm volatile("" : : : "memory");
1587  }
1588 
1589  namespace Detail {
1590  inline void optimizer_barrier() { keep_memory(); }
1591  } // namespace Detail
1592 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
1593 
1594 #pragma optimize("", off)
1595  template <typename T>
1596  inline void keep_memory(T* p) {
1597  // thanks @milleniumbug
1598  *reinterpret_cast<char volatile*>(p) = *reinterpret_cast<char const volatile*>(p);
1599  }
1600  // TODO equivalent keep_memory()
1601 #pragma optimize("", on)
1602 
1603  namespace Detail {
1604  inline void optimizer_barrier() {
1605  std::atomic_thread_fence(std::memory_order_seq_cst);
1606  }
1607  } // namespace Detail
1608 
1609 #endif
1610 
1611  template <typename T>
1612  inline void deoptimize_value(T&& x) {
1613  keep_memory(&x);
1614  }
1615 
1616  template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1617  inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> typename std::enable_if<!std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value>::type {
1618  deoptimize_value(std::forward<Fn>(fn) (std::forward<Args...>(args...)));
1619  }
1620 
1621  template <typename Fn, typename... Args>
1622  inline auto invoke_deoptimized(Fn&& fn, Args&&... args) -> typename std::enable_if<std::is_same<void, decltype(fn(args...))>::value>::type {
1623  std::forward<Fn>(fn) (std::forward<Args...>(args...));
1624  }
1625  } // namespace Benchmark
1626 } // namespace Catch
1627 
1628 #endif // CATCH_OPTIMIZER_HPP_INCLUDED

1666  class ReusableStringStream : Detail::NonCopyable {
1667  std::size_t m_index;
1668  std::ostream* m_oss;
1669  public:
1670  ReusableStringStream();
1671  ~ReusableStringStream();
1672 
1674  std::string str() const;
1676  void str(std::string const& str);
1677 
1678 #if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
1679 #pragma GCC diagnostic push
1680 // Old versions of GCC do not understand -Wnonnull-compare
1681 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wpragmas"
1682 // Streaming a function pointer triggers Waddress and Wnonnull-compare
1683 // on GCC, because it implicitly converts it to bool and then decides
1684 // that the check it uses (a? true : false) is tautological and cannot
1685 // be null...
1686 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Waddress"
1687 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wnonnull-compare"
1688 #endif
1689 
1690  template<typename T>
1691  auto operator << ( T const& value ) -> ReusableStringStream& {
1692  *m_oss << value;
1693  return *this;
1694  }
1695 
1696 #if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__)
1697 #pragma GCC diagnostic pop
1698 #endif
1699  auto get() -> std::ostream& { return *m_oss; }
1700  };
1701 }

1757  struct is_callable_tester {

1759  true_given<decltype(std::declval<Fun>()(std::declval<Args>()...))> static test(int);
1760  template <typename...>
1761  std::false_type static test(...);

1773  // replaced with std::invoke_result here.
1774  template <typename Func, typename... U>
1775  using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::invoke_result_t<Func, U...>>>;
1776 #else
1777  template <typename Func, typename... U>
1778  using FunctionReturnType = std::remove_reference_t<std::remove_cv_t<std::result_of_t<Func(U...)>>>;
1779 #endif

1849 namespace Catch {
1850  namespace Benchmark {
1851  namespace Detail {
1852  template <typename T>
1853  struct CompleteType { using type = T; };
1854  template <>
1855  struct CompleteType<void> { struct type {}; };
1856 
1857  template <typename T>
1858  using CompleteType_t = typename CompleteType<T>::type;
1859 
1860  template <typename Result>
1861  struct CompleteInvoker {
1862  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1863  static Result invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1864  return std::forward<Fun>(fun)(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1865  }
1866  };
1867  template <>
1868  struct CompleteInvoker<void> {
1869  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1870  static CompleteType_t<void> invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1871  std::forward<Fun>(fun)(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1872  return {};
1873  }
1874  };
1875 
1876  // invoke and not return void :(
1877  template <typename Fun, typename... Args>
1878  CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>> complete_invoke(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
1879  return CompleteInvoker<FunctionReturnType<Fun, Args...>>::invoke(std::forward<Fun>(fun), std::forward<Args>(args)...);
1880  }
1881 
1882  extern const std::string benchmarkErrorMsg;
1883  } // namespace Detail
1884 
1885  template <typename Fun>
1886  Detail::CompleteType_t<FunctionReturnType<Fun>> user_code(Fun&& fun) {
1887  CATCH_TRY{
1888  return Detail::complete_invoke(std::forward<Fun>(fun));
1889  } CATCH_CATCH_ALL{
1890  getResultCapture().benchmarkFailed(translateActiveException());
1891  CATCH_RUNTIME_ERROR(Detail::benchmarkErrorMsg);
1892  }
1893  }
1894  } // namespace Benchmark
1895 } // namespace Catch

1902  struct ChronometerConcept {
1903  virtual void start() = 0;
1904  virtual void finish() = 0;
1905  virtual ~ChronometerConcept(); // = default;
1906 
1907  ChronometerConcept() = default;
1908  ChronometerConcept(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1909  ChronometerConcept& operator=(ChronometerConcept const&) = default;
1910  };
1911  template <typename Clock>
1912  struct ChronometerModel final : public ChronometerConcept {
1913  void start() override { started = Clock::now(); }
1914  void finish() override { finished = Clock::now(); }
1915 
1916  ClockDuration<Clock> elapsed() const { return finished - started; }
1917 
1918  TimePoint<Clock> started;
1919  TimePoint<Clock> finished;
1920  };
1921  } // namespace Detail
1922 
1923  struct Chronometer {
1924  public:
1925  template <typename Fun>
1926  void measure(Fun&& fun) { measure(std::forward<Fun>(fun), is_callable<Fun(int)>()); }
1927 
1928  int runs() const { return repeats; }
1929 
1930  Chronometer(Detail::ChronometerConcept& meter, int repeats_)
1931  : impl(&meter)
1932  , repeats(repeats_) {}
1933 
1934  private:
1935  template <typename Fun>
1936  void measure(Fun&& fun, std::false_type) {
1937  measure([&fun](int) { return fun(); }, std::true_type());
1938  }
1939 
1940  template <typename Fun>
1941  void measure(Fun&& fun, std::true_type) {
1942  Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1943  impl->start();
1944  for (int i = 0; i < repeats; ++i) invoke_deoptimized(fun, i);
1945  impl->finish();
1946  Detail::optimizer_barrier();
1947  }
1948 
1949  Detail::ChronometerConcept* impl;
1950  int repeats;
1951  };
1952  } // namespace Benchmark
1953 } // namespace Catch

1997 #ifndef CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED
1998 #define CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED
1999 
2000 
2001 #include <cassert>
2002 #include <type_traits>
2003 #include <utility>
2004 
2005 namespace Catch {
2006  namespace Benchmark {
2007  namespace Detail {
2008  template <typename T>
2009  using Decay = typename std::decay<T>::type;
2010  template <typename T, typename U>
2011  struct is_related
2012  : std::is_same<Decay<T>, Decay<U>> {};
2013 
2021  struct BenchmarkFunction {
2022  private:
2023  struct callable {
2024  virtual void call(Chronometer meter) const = 0;
2025  virtual callable* clone() const = 0;
2026  virtual ~callable(); // = default;
2027 
2028  callable() = default;
2029  callable(callable const&) = default;
2030  callable& operator=(callable const&) = default;
2031  };
2032  template <typename Fun>
2033  struct model : public callable {
2034  model(Fun&& fun_) : fun(std::move(fun_)) {}
2035  model(Fun const& fun_) : fun(fun_) {}
2036 
2037  model<Fun>* clone() const override { return new model<Fun>(*this); }
2038 
2039  void call(Chronometer meter) const override {
2040  call(meter, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
2041  }
2042  void call(Chronometer meter, std::true_type) const {
2043  fun(meter);
2044  }
2045  void call(Chronometer meter, std::false_type) const {
2046  meter.measure(fun);
2047  }
2048 
2049  Fun fun;
2050  };
2051 
2052  struct do_nothing { void operator()() const {} };
2053 
2054  template <typename T>
2055  BenchmarkFunction(model<T>* c) : f(c) {}
2056 
2057  public:
2058  BenchmarkFunction()
2059  : f(new model<do_nothing>{ {} }) {}
2060 
2061  template <typename Fun,
2062  typename std::enable_if<!is_related<Fun, BenchmarkFunction>::value, int>::type = 0>
2063  BenchmarkFunction(Fun&& fun)
2064  : f(new model<typename std::decay<Fun>::type>(std::forward<Fun>(fun))) {}
2065 
2066  BenchmarkFunction( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept:
2067  f( std::move( that.f ) ) {}
2068 
2069  BenchmarkFunction(BenchmarkFunction const& that)
2070  : f(that.f->clone()) {}
2071 
2072  BenchmarkFunction&
2073  operator=( BenchmarkFunction&& that ) noexcept {
2074  f = std::move( that.f );
2075  return *this;
2076  }
2077 
2078  BenchmarkFunction& operator=(BenchmarkFunction const& that) {
2079  f.reset(that.f->clone());
2080  return *this;
2081  }
2082 
2083  void operator()(Chronometer meter) const { f->call(meter); }
2084 
2085  private:
2086  Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<callable> f;
2087  };
2088  } // namespace Detail
2089  } // namespace Benchmark
2090 } // namespace Catch
2091 
2092 #endif // CATCH_BENCHMARK_FUNCTION_HPP_INCLUDED

2097 #ifndef CATCH_REPEAT_HPP_INCLUDED

2099 
2100 #include <type_traits>
2101 #include <utility>
2102 
2103 namespace Catch {
2104  namespace Benchmark {
2105  namespace Detail {
2106  template <typename Fun>
2107  struct repeater {
2108  void operator()(int k) const {
2109  for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2110  fun();
2111  }
2112  }
2113  Fun fun;
2114  };
2115  template <typename Fun>
2116  repeater<typename std::decay<Fun>::type> repeat(Fun&& fun) {
2117  return { std::forward<Fun>(fun) };
2118  }
2119  } // namespace Detail

2168  template <typename Clock, typename Fun, typename... Args>
2169  TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Args...> measure(Fun&& fun, Args&&... args) {
2170  auto start = Clock::now();
2171  auto&& r = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, std::forward<Args>(args)...);
2172  auto end = Clock::now();
2173  auto delta = end - start;
2174  return { delta, std::forward<decltype(r)>(r), 1 };
2175  }

2186  namespace Benchmark {
2187  namespace Detail {
2188  template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2189  TimingOf<Clock, Fun, int> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::false_type) {
2190  return Detail::measure<Clock>(fun, iters);
2191  }
2192  template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2193  TimingOf<Clock, Fun, Chronometer> measure_one(Fun&& fun, int iters, std::true_type) {
2194  Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> meter;
2195  auto&& result = Detail::complete_invoke(fun, Chronometer(meter, iters));
2196 
2197  return { meter.elapsed(), std::move(result), iters };
2198  }
2199 
2200  template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2201  using run_for_at_least_argument_t = typename std::conditional<is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>::value, Chronometer, int>::type;
2202 
2203 
2204  [[noreturn]]
2205  void throw_optimized_away_error();
2206 
2207  template <typename Clock, typename Fun>
2208  TimingOf<Clock, Fun, run_for_at_least_argument_t<Clock, Fun>> run_for_at_least(ClockDuration<Clock> how_long, int seed, Fun&& fun) {
2209  auto iters = seed;
2210  while (iters < (1 << 30)) {
2211  auto&& Timing = measure_one<Clock>(fun, iters, is_callable<Fun(Chronometer)>());
2212 
2213  if (Timing.elapsed >= how_long) {
2214  return { Timing.elapsed, std::move(Timing.result), iters };
2215  }
2216  iters *= 2;
2217  }
2218  throw_optimized_away_error();
2219  }
2220  } // namespace Detail
2221  } // namespace Benchmark
2222 } // namespace Catch

2230  template <typename Duration>
2231  struct ExecutionPlan {
2232  int iterations_per_sample;
2233  Duration estimated_duration;
2234  Detail::BenchmarkFunction benchmark;
2235  Duration warmup_time;
2236  int warmup_iterations;
2237 
2238  template <typename Duration2>
2239  operator ExecutionPlan<Duration2>() const {
2240  return { iterations_per_sample, estimated_duration, benchmark, warmup_time, warmup_iterations };
2241  }
2242 
2243  template <typename Clock>
2244  std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> run(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
2245  // warmup a bit
2246  Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_iterations, Detail::repeat(now<Clock>{}));
2247 
2248  std::vector<FloatDuration<Clock>> times;
2249  times.reserve(cfg.benchmarkSamples());
2250  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), cfg.benchmarkSamples(), [this, env] {
2251  Detail::ChronometerModel<Clock> model;
2252  this->benchmark(Chronometer(model, iterations_per_sample));
2253  auto sample_time = model.elapsed() - env.clock_cost.mean;
2254  if (sample_time < FloatDuration<Clock>::zero()) sample_time = FloatDuration<Clock>::zero();
2255  return sample_time / iterations_per_sample;
2256  });
2257  return times;
2258  }
2259  };

2279 #include <algorithm>

2286 namespace Catch {
2287  namespace Benchmark {
2288  namespace Detail {
2289  using sample = std::vector<double>;
2290 
2291  double weighted_average_quantile(int k, int q, std::vector<double>::iterator first, std::vector<double>::iterator last);
2292 
2293  template <typename Iterator>
2294  OutlierClassification classify_outliers(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2295  std::vector<double> copy(first, last);
2296 
2297  auto q1 = weighted_average_quantile(1, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
2298  auto q3 = weighted_average_quantile(3, 4, copy.begin(), copy.end());
2299  auto iqr = q3 - q1;
2300  auto los = q1 - (iqr * 3.);
2301  auto lom = q1 - (iqr * 1.5);
2302  auto him = q3 + (iqr * 1.5);
2303  auto his = q3 + (iqr * 3.);
2304 
2305  OutlierClassification o;
2306  for (; first != last; ++first) {
2307  auto&& t = *first;
2308  if (t < los) ++o.low_severe;
2309  else if (t < lom) ++o.low_mild;
2310  else if (t > his) ++o.high_severe;
2311  else if (t > him) ++o.high_mild;
2312  ++o.samples_seen;
2313  }
2314  return o;
2315  }
2316 
2317  template <typename Iterator>
2318  double mean(Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2319  auto count = last - first;
2320  double sum = std::accumulate(first, last, 0.);
2321  return sum / count;
2322  }
2323 
2324  template <typename Estimator, typename Iterator>
2325  sample jackknife(Estimator&& estimator, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2326  auto n = last - first;
2327  auto second = first;
2328  ++second;
2329  sample results;
2330  results.reserve(n);
2331 
2332  for (auto it = first; it != last; ++it) {
2333  std::iter_swap(it, first);
2334  results.push_back(estimator(second, last));
2335  }
2336 
2337  return results;
2338  }
2339 
2340  inline double normal_cdf(double x) {
2341  return std::erfc(-x / std::sqrt(2.0)) / 2.0;
2342  }
2343 
2344  double erfc_inv(double x);
2345 
2346  double normal_quantile(double p);
2347 
2348  template <typename Iterator, typename Estimator>
2349  Estimate<double> bootstrap(double confidence_level, Iterator first, Iterator last, sample const& resample, Estimator&& estimator) {
2350  auto n_samples = last - first;
2351 
2352  double point = estimator(first, last);
2353  // Degenerate case with a single sample
2354  if (n_samples == 1) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
2355 
2356  sample jack = jackknife(estimator, first, last);
2357  double jack_mean = mean(jack.begin(), jack.end());
2358  double sum_squares, sum_cubes;
2359  std::tie(sum_squares, sum_cubes) = std::accumulate(jack.begin(), jack.end(), std::make_pair(0., 0.), [jack_mean](std::pair<double, double> sqcb, double x) -> std::pair<double, double> {
2360  auto d = jack_mean - x;
2361  auto d2 = d * d;
2362  auto d3 = d2 * d;
2363  return { sqcb.first + d2, sqcb.second + d3 };
2364  });
2365 
2366  double accel = sum_cubes / (6 * std::pow(sum_squares, 1.5));
2367  int n = static_cast<int>(resample.size());
2368  double prob_n = std::count_if(resample.begin(), resample.end(), [point](double x) { return x < point; }) / (double)n;
2369  // degenerate case with uniform samples
2370  if (prob_n == 0) return { point, point, point, confidence_level };
2371 
2372  double bias = normal_quantile(prob_n);
2373  double z1 = normal_quantile((1. - confidence_level) / 2.);
2374 
2375  auto cumn = [n](double x) -> int {
2376  return std::lround(normal_cdf(x) * n); };
2377  auto a = [bias, accel](double b) { return bias + b / (1. - accel * b); };
2378  double b1 = bias + z1;
2379  double b2 = bias - z1;
2380  double a1 = a(b1);
2381  double a2 = a(b2);
2382  auto lo = std::max(cumn(a1), 0);
2383  auto hi = std::min(cumn(a2), n - 1);
2384 
2385  return { point, resample[lo], resample[hi], confidence_level };
2386  }
2387 
2388  double outlier_variance(Estimate<double> mean, Estimate<double> stddev, int n);
2389 
2390  struct bootstrap_analysis {
2391  Estimate<double> mean;
2392  Estimate<double> standard_deviation;
2393  double outlier_variance;
2394  };
2395 
2396  bootstrap_analysis analyse_samples(double confidence_level, int n_resamples, std::vector<double>::iterator first, std::vector<double>::iterator last);
2397  } // namespace Detail
2398  } // namespace Benchmark

2408 namespace Catch {
2409  namespace Benchmark {
2410  namespace Detail {
2411  template <typename Clock>
2412  std::vector<double> resolution(int k) {
2413  std::vector<TimePoint<Clock>> times;
2414  times.reserve(k + 1);
2415  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), k + 1, now<Clock>{});
2416 
2417  std::vector<double> deltas;
2418  deltas.reserve(k);
2419  std::transform(std::next(times.begin()), times.end(), times.begin(),
2420  std::back_inserter(deltas),
2421  [](TimePoint<Clock> a, TimePoint<Clock> b) { return static_cast<double>((a - b).count()); });
2422 
2423  return deltas;
2424  }
2425 
2426  const auto warmup_iterations = 10000;
2427  const auto warmup_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(100);
2428  const auto minimum_ticks = 1000;
2429  const auto warmup_seed = 10000;
2430  const auto clock_resolution_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(500);
2431  const auto clock_cost_estimation_time_limit = std::chrono::seconds(1);
2432  const auto clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit = 100000;
2433  const auto clock_cost_estimation_time = std::chrono::milliseconds(10);
2434  const auto clock_cost_estimation_iterations = 10000;
2435 
2436  template <typename Clock>
2437  int warmup() {
2438  return run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(warmup_time), warmup_seed, &resolution<Clock>)
2439  .iterations;
2440  }
2441  template <typename Clock>
2442  EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_resolution(int iterations) {
2443  auto r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_resolution_estimation_time), iterations, &resolution<Clock>)
2444  .result;
2445  return {
2446  FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(r.begin(), r.end())),
2447  classify_outliers(r.begin(), r.end()),
2448  };
2449  }
2450  template <typename Clock>
2451  EnvironmentEstimate<FloatDuration<Clock>> estimate_clock_cost(FloatDuration<Clock> resolution) {
2452  auto time_limit = std::min(resolution * clock_cost_estimation_tick_limit, FloatDuration<Clock>(clock_cost_estimation_time_limit));
2453  auto time_clock = [](int k) {
2454  return Detail::measure<Clock>([k] {
2455  for (int i = 0; i < k; ++i) {
2456  volatile auto ignored = Clock::now();
2457  (void)ignored;
2458  }
2459  }).elapsed;
2460  };
2461  time_clock(1);
2462  int iters = clock_cost_estimation_iterations;
2463  auto&& r = run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(clock_cost_estimation_time), iters, time_clock);
2464  std::vector<double> times;
2465  int nsamples = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(time_limit / r.elapsed));
2466  times.reserve(nsamples);
2467  std::generate_n(std::back_inserter(times), nsamples, [time_clock, &r] {
2468  return static_cast<double>((time_clock(r.iterations) / r.iterations).count());
2469  });
2470  return {
2471  FloatDuration<Clock>(mean(times.begin(), times.end())),
2472  classify_outliers(times.begin(), times.end()),
2473  };
2474  }
2475 
2476  template <typename Clock>
2477  Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> measure_environment() {
2478  static Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>* env = nullptr;
2479  if (env) {
2480  return *env;
2481  }
2482 
2483  auto iters = Detail::warmup<Clock>();
2484  auto resolution = Detail::estimate_clock_resolution<Clock>(iters);
2485  auto cost = Detail::estimate_clock_cost<Clock>(resolution.mean);
2486 
2487  env = new Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>>{ resolution, cost };
2488  return *env;
2489  }

2548 namespace Catch {
2549  namespace Benchmark {
2550  namespace Detail {
2551  template <typename Duration, typename Iterator>
2552  SampleAnalysis<Duration> analyse(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<Duration>, Iterator first, Iterator last) {
2553  if (!cfg.benchmarkNoAnalysis()) {
2554  std::vector<double> samples;
2555  samples.reserve(last - first);
2556  std::transform(first, last, std::back_inserter(samples), [](Duration d) { return d.count(); });
2557 
2558  auto analysis = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::analyse_samples(cfg.benchmarkConfidenceInterval(), cfg.benchmarkResamples(), samples.begin(), samples.end());
2559  auto outliers = Catch::Benchmark::Detail::classify_outliers(samples.begin(), samples.end());
2560 
2561  auto wrap_estimate = [](Estimate<double> e) {
2562  return Estimate<Duration> {
2563  Duration(e.point),
2564  Duration(e.lower_bound),
2565  Duration(e.upper_bound),
2566  e.confidence_interval,
2567  };
2568  };
2569  std::vector<Duration> samples2;
2570  samples2.reserve(samples.size());
2571  std::transform(samples.begin(), samples.end(), std::back_inserter(samples2), [](double d) { return Duration(d); });
2572  return {
2573  std::move(samples2),
2574  wrap_estimate(analysis.mean),
2575  wrap_estimate(analysis.standard_deviation),
2576  outliers,
2577  analysis.outlier_variance,
2578  };
2579  } else {
2580  std::vector<Duration> samples;
2581  samples.reserve(last - first);
2582 
2583  Duration mean = Duration(0);
2584  int i = 0;
2585  for (auto it = first; it < last; ++it, ++i) {
2586  samples.push_back(Duration(*it));
2587  mean += Duration(*it);
2588  }
2589  mean /= i;
2590 
2591  return {
2592  std::move(samples),
2593  Estimate<Duration>{mean, mean, mean, 0.0},
2594  Estimate<Duration>{Duration(0), Duration(0), Duration(0), 0.0},
2595  OutlierClassification{},
2596  0.0
2597  };
2598  }
2599  }

2614  struct Benchmark {
2615  Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName)
2616  : name(std::move(benchmarkName)) {}
2617

2619  Benchmark(std::string&& benchmarkName , FUN &&func)

2621 
2622  template <typename Clock>
2623  ExecutionPlan<FloatDuration<Clock>> prepare(const IConfig &cfg, Environment<FloatDuration<Clock>> env) const {
2624  auto min_time = env.clock_resolution.mean * Detail::minimum_ticks;
2625  auto run_time = std::max(min_time, std::chrono::duration_cast<decltype(min_time)>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()));
2626  auto&& test = Detail::run_for_at_least<Clock>(std::chrono::duration_cast<ClockDuration<Clock>>(run_time), 1, fun);
2627  int new_iters = static_cast<int>(std::ceil(min_time * test.iterations / test.elapsed));
2628  return { new_iters, test.elapsed / test.iterations * new_iters * cfg.benchmarkSamples(), fun, std::chrono::duration_cast<FloatDuration<Clock>>(cfg.benchmarkWarmupTime()), Detail::warmup_iterations };
2629  }
2630 
2631  template <typename Clock = default_clock>
2632  void run() {
2633  auto const* cfg = getCurrentContext().getConfig();
2634 
2635  auto env = Detail::measure_environment<Clock>();
2636 
2637  getResultCapture().benchmarkPreparing(name);
2638  CATCH_TRY{
2639  auto plan = user_code([&] {
2640  return prepare<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2641  });
2642 
2643  BenchmarkInfo info {
2644  name,
2645  plan.estimated_duration.count(),
2646  plan.iterations_per_sample,
2647  cfg->benchmarkSamples(),
2648  cfg->benchmarkResamples(),
2649  env.clock_resolution.mean.count(),
2650  env.clock_cost.mean.count()
2651  };
2652 
2653  getResultCapture().benchmarkStarting(info);
2654 
2655  auto samples = user_code([&] {
2656  return plan.template run<Clock>(*cfg, env);
2657  });
2658 
2659  auto analysis = Detail::analyse(*cfg, env, samples.begin(), samples.end());
2660  BenchmarkStats<FloatDuration<Clock>> stats{ info, analysis.samples, analysis.mean, analysis.standard_deviation, analysis.outliers, analysis.outlier_variance };
2661  getResultCapture().benchmarkEnded(stats);
2662 
2663  } CATCH_CATCH_ALL{
2664  if (translateActiveException() != Detail::benchmarkErrorMsg) // benchmark errors have been reported, otherwise rethrow.
2665  std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
2666  }
2667  }
2668 
2669  // sets lambda to be used in fun *and* executes benchmark!
2670  template <typename Fun,
2671  typename std::enable_if<!Detail::is_related<Fun, Benchmark>::value, int>::type = 0>
2672  Benchmark & operator=(Fun func) {
2673  fun = Detail::BenchmarkFunction(func);
2674  run();
2675  return *this;
2676  }
2677 
2678  explicit operator bool() {
2679  return true;
2680  }
2681 
2682  private:
2683  Detail::BenchmarkFunction fun;
2684  std::string name;
2685  };
2686  }

2711 #define BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(name) \
2712  INTERNAL_CATCH_BENCHMARK_ADVANCED(INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME(____C_A_T_C_H____B_E_N_C_H____), name)
2713 
2714 #endif

2722 #define CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2724 #include <type_traits>
2725 
2726 namespace Catch {
2727  namespace Benchmark {
2728  namespace Detail {
2729  template <typename T, bool Destruct>
2730  struct ObjectStorage
2731  {
2732  using TStorage = typename std::aligned_storage<sizeof(T), std::alignment_of<T>::value>::type;
2733 
2734  ObjectStorage() : data() {}
2735 
2736  ObjectStorage(const ObjectStorage& other)
2737  {
2738  new(&data) T(other.stored_object());
2739  }
2740 
2741  ObjectStorage(ObjectStorage&& other)
2742  {
2743  new(&data) T(std::move(other.stored_object()));
2744  }
2745 
2746  ~ObjectStorage() { destruct_on_exit<T>(); }
2747 
2748  template <typename... Args>
2749  void construct(Args&&... args)
2750  {
2751  new (&data) T(std::forward<Args>(args)...);
2752  }
2753 
2754  template <bool AllowManualDestruction = !Destruct>
2755  typename std::enable_if<AllowManualDestruction>::type destruct()
2756  {
2757  stored_object().~T();
2758  }
2759 
2760  private:
2761  // If this is a constructor benchmark, destruct the underlying object
2762  template <typename U>
2763  void destruct_on_exit(typename std::enable_if<Destruct, U>::type* = 0) { destruct<true>(); }
2764  // Otherwise, don't
2765  template <typename U>
2766  void destruct_on_exit(typename std::enable_if<!Destruct, U>::type* = 0) { }
2767 
2768  T& stored_object() {
2769  return *static_cast<T*>(static_cast<void*>(&data));
2770  }
2771 
2772  T const& stored_object() const {
2773  return *static_cast<T*>(static_cast<void*>(&data));
2774  }
2775 
2776 
2777  TStorage data;
2778  };
2779  } // namespace Detail
2780 
2781  template <typename T>
2782  using storage_for = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, true>;
2783 
2784  template <typename T>
2785  using destructable_object = Detail::ObjectStorage<T, false>;
2786  } // namespace Benchmark
2787 } // namespace Catch
2788 
2789 #endif // CATCH_CONSTRUCTOR_HPP_INCLUDED

2791 #endif // CATCH_BENCHMARK_ALL_HPP_INCLUDED

2828  struct IMutableEnumValuesRegistry {
2829  virtual ~IMutableEnumValuesRegistry();
2830 
2831  virtual Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::vector<int> const& values ) = 0;
2832 
2833  template<typename E>
2834  Detail::EnumInfo const& registerEnum( StringRef enumName, StringRef allEnums, std::initializer_list<E> values ) {
2835  static_assert(sizeof(int) >= sizeof(E), "Cannot serialize enum to int");
2836  std::vector<int> intValues;
2837  intValues.reserve( values.size() );
2838  for( auto enumValue : values )
2839  intValues.push_back( static_cast<int>( enumValue ) );
2840  return registerEnum( enumName, allEnums, intValues );
2841  }
2842  };

2869  template<typename T>
2870  class IsStreamInsertable {
2871  template<typename Stream, typename U>
2872  static auto test(int)
2873  -> decltype(std::declval<Stream&>() << std::declval<U>(), std::true_type());
2874 
2875  template<typename, typename>
2876  static auto test(...)->std::false_type;
2877 
2878  public:
2879  static const bool value = decltype(test<std::ostream, const T&>(0))::value;
2880  };

2923  struct StringMaker {
2924  template <typename Fake = T>
2925  static
2926  std::enable_if_t<::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
2927  convert(const Fake& value) {

2929  // NB: call using the function-like syntax to avoid ambiguity with
2930  // user-defined templated operator<< under clang.
2931  rss.operator<<(value);
2932  return rss.str();
2933  }

2936  static
2937  std::enable_if_t<!::Catch::Detail::IsStreamInsertable<Fake>::value, std::string>
2938  convert( const Fake& value ) {
2939 #if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER)
2940  return Detail::convertUnstreamable(value);
2941 #else
2942  return CATCH_CONFIG_FALLBACK_STRINGIFIER(value);
2943 #endif
2944  }
2945  };

3141  namespace Detail {
3142  template<typename InputIterator, typename Sentinel = InputIterator>
3143  std::string rangeToString(InputIterator first, Sentinel last) {
3144  ReusableStringStream rss;
3145  rss << "{ ";
3146  if (first != last) {
3147  rss << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
3148  for (++first; first != last; ++first)
3149  rss << ", " << ::Catch::Detail::stringify(*first);
3150  }
3151  rss << " }";
3152  return rss.str();
3153  }
3154  }
3155 
3156 } // namespace Catch

3406  };
3407  template<typename Value>
3408  struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<60>>> {
3409  static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<60>> const& duration) {
3410  ReusableStringStream rss;
3411  rss << duration.count() << " m";
3412  return rss.str();
3413  }
3414  };
3415  template<typename Value>
3416  struct StringMaker<std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<3600>>> {
3417  static std::string convert(std::chrono::duration<Value, std::ratio<3600>> const& duration) {
3418  ReusableStringStream rss;
3419  rss << duration.count() << " h";
3420  return rss.str();
3421  }
3422  };
3423 
3425  // std::chrono::time_point specialization
3426  // Generic time_point cannot be specialized, only std::chrono::time_point<system_clock>
3427  template<typename Clock, typename Duration>
3428  struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration>> {
3429  static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<Clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3430  return ::Catch::Detail::stringify(time_point.time_since_epoch()) + " since epoch";
3431  }
3432  };
3433  // std::chrono::time_point<system_clock> specialization
3434  template<typename Duration>
3435  struct StringMaker<std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration>> {
3436  static std::string convert(std::chrono::time_point<std::chrono::system_clock, Duration> const& time_point) {
3437  auto converted = std::chrono::system_clock::to_time_t(time_point);
3438 
3439 #ifdef _MSC_VER
3440  std::tm timeInfo = {};
3441  gmtime_s(&timeInfo, &converted);
3442 #else
3443  std::tm* timeInfo = std::gmtime(&converted);
3444 #endif
3445 
3446  auto const timeStampSize = sizeof("2017-01-16T17:06:45Z");
3447  char timeStamp[timeStampSize];
3448  const char * const fmt = "%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ";
3449 
3450 #ifdef _MSC_VER
3451  std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, &timeInfo);
3452 #else
3453  std::strftime(timeStamp, timeStampSize, fmt, timeInfo);
3454 #endif
3455  return std::string(timeStamp);
3456  }
3457  };
3458 }

3461 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_REGISTER_ENUM( enumName, ... ) \
3462 namespace Catch { \
3463  template<> struct StringMaker<enumName> { \
3464  static std::string convert( enumName value ) { \
3465  static const auto& enumInfo = ::Catch::getMutableRegistryHub().getMutableEnumValuesRegistry().registerEnum( #enumName, #__VA_ARGS__, { __VA_ARGS__ } ); \
3466  return static_cast<std::string>(enumInfo.lookup( static_cast<int>( value ) )); \
3467  } \
3468  }; \
3469 }

3483  class Approx {
3484  private:
3485  bool equalityComparisonImpl(double other) const;
3486  // Sets and validates the new margin (margin >= 0)
3487  void setMargin(double margin);
3488  // Sets and validates the new epsilon (0 < epsilon < 1)
3489  void setEpsilon(double epsilon);
3490 
3491  public:
3492  explicit Approx ( double value );
3493 
3494  static Approx custom();
3495 
3496  Approx operator-() const;
3497 
3498  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3499  Approx operator()( T const& value ) {
3500  Approx approx( static_cast<double>(value) );
3501  approx.m_epsilon = m_epsilon;
3502  approx.m_margin = m_margin;
3503  approx.m_scale = m_scale;
3504  return approx;
3505  }
3506 
3507  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3508  explicit Approx( T const& value ): Approx(static_cast<double>(value))
3509  {}
3510 
3511 
3512  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3513  friend bool operator == ( const T& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3514  auto lhs_v = static_cast<double>(lhs);
3515  return rhs.equalityComparisonImpl(lhs_v);
3516  }
3517 
3518  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3519  friend bool operator == ( Approx const& lhs, const T& rhs ) {
3520  return operator==( rhs, lhs );
3521  }
3522 
3523  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3524  friend bool operator != ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3525  return !operator==( lhs, rhs );
3526  }
3527 
3528  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3529  friend bool operator != ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3530  return !operator==( rhs, lhs );
3531  }
3532 
3533  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3534  friend bool operator <= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3535  return static_cast<double>(lhs) < rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3536  }
3537 
3538  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3539  friend bool operator <= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3540  return lhs.m_value < static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3541  }
3542 
3543  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3544  friend bool operator >= ( T const& lhs, Approx const& rhs ) {
3545  return static_cast<double>(lhs) > rhs.m_value || lhs == rhs;
3546  }
3547 
3548  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3549  friend bool operator >= ( Approx const& lhs, T const& rhs ) {
3550  return lhs.m_value > static_cast<double>(rhs) || lhs == rhs;
3551  }
3552 
3553  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3554  Approx& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
3555  double epsilonAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newEpsilon);
3556  setEpsilon(epsilonAsDouble);
3557  return *this;
3558  }
3559 
3560  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3561  Approx& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
3562  double marginAsDouble = static_cast<double>(newMargin);
3563  setMargin(marginAsDouble);
3564  return *this;
3565  }
3566 
3567  template <typename T, typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
3568  Approx& scale( T const& newScale ) {
3569  m_scale = static_cast<double>(newScale);
3570  return *this;
3571  }
3572 
3573  std::string toString() const;
3574 
3575  private:
3576  double m_epsilon;
3577  double m_margin;
3578  double m_scale;
3579  double m_value;
3580  };

3913 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_MSG( macroName, messageType, resultDisposition, ... ) \
3914  do { \
3915  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), resultDisposition ); \
3916  catchAssertionHandler.handleMessage( messageType, ( Catch::MessageStream() << __VA_ARGS__ + ::Catch::StreamEndStop() ).m_stream.str() ); \
3917  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
3918  } while( false )
3919 
3921 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_CAPTURE( varName, macroName, ... ) \
3922  Catch::Capturer varName( macroName, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info, #__VA_ARGS__ ); \
3923  varName.captureValues( 0, __VA_ARGS__ )
3924 
3926 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_INFO( macroName, log ) \
3927  Catch::ScopedMessage INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( scopedMessage )( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )
3928 
3930 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_UNSCOPED_INFO( macroName, log ) \
3931  Catch::getResultCapture().emplaceUnscopedMessage( Catch::MessageBuilder( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::ResultWas::Info ) << log )

4120  // Traits for extracting arg and return type of lambdas (for single
4121  // argument lambdas)
4122  template <typename L>
4123  struct UnaryLambdaTraits
4124  : UnaryLambdaTraits<decltype( &L::operator() )> {};
4125 
4126  template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename... Args>
4127  struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( Args... ) const> {
4128  static const bool isValid = false;
4129  };
4130 
4131  template <typename ClassT, typename ReturnT, typename ArgT>
4132  struct UnaryLambdaTraits<ReturnT ( ClassT::* )( ArgT ) const> {
4133  static const bool isValid = true;
4134  using ArgType = typename std::remove_const<
4135  typename std::remove_reference<ArgT>::type>::type;
4136  using ReturnType = ReturnT;
4137  };
4138 
4139  class TokenStream;
4140 
4141  // Wraps a token coming from a token stream. These may not directly
4142  // correspond to strings as a single string may encode an option +
4143  // its argument if the : or = form is used
4144  enum class TokenType { Option, Argument };
4145  struct Token {
4146  TokenType type;
4147  std::string token;
4148  };
4149 
4150  // Abstracts iterators into args as a stream of tokens, with option
4151  // arguments uniformly handled
4152  class TokenStream {
4153  using Iterator = std::vector<std::string>::const_iterator;
4154  Iterator it;
4155  Iterator itEnd;
4156  std::vector<Token> m_tokenBuffer;
4157 
4158  void loadBuffer();
4159 
4160  public:
4161  explicit TokenStream( Args const& args );
4162  TokenStream( Iterator it, Iterator itEnd );
4163 
4164  explicit operator bool() const {
4165  return !m_tokenBuffer.empty() || it != itEnd;
4166  }
4167 
4168  size_t count() const {
4169  return m_tokenBuffer.size() + ( itEnd - it );
4170  }
4171 
4172  Token operator*() const {
4173  assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4174  return m_tokenBuffer.front();
4175  }
4176 
4177  Token const* operator->() const {
4178  assert( !m_tokenBuffer.empty() );
4179  return &m_tokenBuffer.front();
4180  }
4181 
4182  TokenStream& operator++();
4183  };
4184 
4186  enum class ResultType {
4187  Ok,
4188  LogicError,
4189  RuntimeError
4191  };
4192 
4193  class ResultBase {
4194  protected:
4195  ResultBase( ResultType type ): m_type( type ) {}
4196  virtual ~ResultBase(); // = default;
4197 
4198 
4199  ResultBase(ResultBase const&) = default;
4200  ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase const&) = default;
4201  ResultBase(ResultBase&&) = default;
4202  ResultBase& operator=(ResultBase&&) = default;
4203 
4204  virtual void enforceOk() const = 0;
4205 
4206  ResultType m_type;
4207  };
4208 
4209  template <typename T> class ResultValueBase : public ResultBase {
4210  public:
4211  auto value() const -> T const& {
4212  enforceOk();
4213  return m_value;
4214  }
4215 
4216  protected:
4217  ResultValueBase( ResultType type ): ResultBase( type ) {}
4218 
4219  ResultValueBase( ResultValueBase const& other ):
4220  ResultBase( other ) {
4221  if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4222  new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4223  }
4224 
4225  ResultValueBase( ResultType, T const& value ): ResultBase( ResultType::Ok ) {
4226  new ( &m_value ) T( value );
4227  }
4228 
4229  auto operator=( ResultValueBase const& other )
4230  -> ResultValueBase& {
4231  if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4232  m_value.~T();
4233  ResultBase::operator=( other );
4234  if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4235  new ( &m_value ) T( other.m_value );
4236  return *this;
4237  }
4238 
4239  ~ResultValueBase() override {
4240  if ( m_type == ResultType::Ok )
4241  m_value.~T();
4242  }
4243 
4244  union {
4245  T m_value;
4246  };
4247  };
4248 
4249  template <> class ResultValueBase<void> : public ResultBase {
4250  protected:
4251  using ResultBase::ResultBase;
4252  };
4253 
4254  template <typename T = void>
4255  class BasicResult : public ResultValueBase<T> {
4256  public:
4257  template <typename U>
4258  explicit BasicResult( BasicResult<U> const& other ):
4259  ResultValueBase<T>( other.type() ),
4260  m_errorMessage( other.errorMessage() ) {
4261  assert( type() != ResultType::Ok );
4262  }
4263 
4264  template <typename U>
4265  static auto ok( U const& value ) -> BasicResult {
4266  return { ResultType::Ok, value };
4267  }
4268  static auto ok() -> BasicResult { return { ResultType::Ok }; }
4269  static auto logicError( std::string const& message )
4270  -> BasicResult {
4271  return { ResultType::LogicError, message };
4272  }
4273  static auto runtimeError( std::string const& message )
4274  -> BasicResult {
4275  return { ResultType::RuntimeError, message };
4276  }
4277 
4278  explicit operator bool() const {
4279  return m_type == ResultType::Ok;
4280  }
4281  auto type() const -> ResultType { return m_type; }
4282  auto errorMessage() const -> std::string {
4283  return m_errorMessage;
4284  }
4285 
4286  protected:
4287  void enforceOk() const override {
4288 
4289  // Errors shouldn't reach this point, but if they do
4290  // the actual error message will be in m_errorMessage
4291  assert( m_type != ResultType::LogicError );
4292  assert( m_type != ResultType::RuntimeError );
4293  if ( m_type != ResultType::Ok )
4294  std::abort();
4295  }
4296 
4297  std::string
4298  m_errorMessage; // Only populated if resultType is an error
4299 
4300  BasicResult( ResultType type,
4301  std::string const& message ):
4302  ResultValueBase<T>( type ), m_errorMessage( message ) {
4303  assert( m_type != ResultType::Ok );
4304  }
4305 
4306  using ResultValueBase<T>::ResultValueBase;
4307  using ResultBase::m_type;
4308  };

4310  class ParseState {
4311  public:
4312  ParseState( ParseResultType type,
4313  TokenStream const& remainingTokens );
4314 
4315  ParseResultType type() const { return m_type; }
4316  TokenStream const& remainingTokens() const {
4317  return m_remainingTokens;
4318  }
4319 
4320  private:
4321  ParseResultType m_type;
4322  TokenStream m_remainingTokens;
4323  };

4326  using ParserResult = BasicResult<ParseResultType>;
4327  using InternalParseResult = BasicResult<ParseState>;

4329  struct HelpColumns {

4331  std::string right;

4333 
4334  template <typename T>
4335  ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, T& target ) {
4336  std::stringstream ss( source );
4337  ss >> target;
4338  if ( ss.fail() ) {
4339  return ParserResult::runtimeError(
4340  "Unable to convert '" + source +
4341  "' to destination type" );
4342  } else {
4343  return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4344  }
4345  }
4346  ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source,
4347  std::string& target );
4348  ParserResult convertInto( std::string const& source, bool& target );
4349 
4350 #ifdef CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE
4351  template <typename T>
4352  auto convertInto( std::string const& source,
4353  CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE<T>& target )
4354  -> ParserResult {
4355  T temp;
4356  auto result = convertInto( source, temp );
4357  if ( result )
4358  target = std::move( temp );
4359  return result;
4360  }
4361 #endif // CLARA_CONFIG_OPTIONAL_TYPE

4363  struct BoundRef : Catch::Detail::NonCopyable {
4364  virtual ~BoundRef() = default;
4365  virtual bool isContainer() const;
4366  virtual bool isFlag() const;
4367  };
4368  struct BoundValueRefBase : BoundRef {
4369  virtual auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4370  -> ParserResult = 0;
4371  };
4372  struct BoundFlagRefBase : BoundRef {
4373  virtual auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult = 0;
4374  bool isFlag() const override;
4375  };
4376 
4377  template <typename T> struct BoundValueRef : BoundValueRefBase {
4378  T& m_ref;
4379 
4380  explicit BoundValueRef( T& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4381 
4382  ParserResult setValue( std::string const& arg ) override {
4383  return convertInto( arg, m_ref );
4384  }
4385  };
4386 
4387  template <typename T>
4388  struct BoundValueRef<std::vector<T>> : BoundValueRefBase {
4389  std::vector<T>& m_ref;
4390 
4391  explicit BoundValueRef( std::vector<T>& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4392 
4393  auto isContainer() const -> bool override { return true; }
4394 
4395  auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4396  -> ParserResult override {
4397  T temp;
4398  auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4399  if ( result )
4400  m_ref.push_back( temp );
4401  return result;
4402  }
4403  };
4404 
4405  struct BoundFlagRef : BoundFlagRefBase {
4406  bool& m_ref;
4407 
4408  explicit BoundFlagRef( bool& ref ): m_ref( ref ) {}
4409 
4410  ParserResult setFlag( bool flag ) override;
4411  };
4412 
4413  template <typename ReturnType> struct LambdaInvoker {
4414  static_assert(
4415  std::is_same<ReturnType, ParserResult>::value,
4416  "Lambda must return void or clara::ParserResult" );
4417 
4418  template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4419  static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4420  -> ParserResult {
4421  return lambda( arg );
4422  }
4423  };
4424 
4425  template <> struct LambdaInvoker<void> {
4426  template <typename L, typename ArgType>
4427  static auto invoke( L const& lambda, ArgType const& arg )
4428  -> ParserResult {
4429  lambda( arg );
4430  return ParserResult::ok( ParseResultType::Matched );
4431  }
4432  };
4433 
4434  template <typename ArgType, typename L>
4435  auto invokeLambda( L const& lambda, std::string const& arg )
4436  -> ParserResult {
4437  ArgType temp{};
4438  auto result = convertInto( arg, temp );
4439  return !result ? result
4440  : LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4441  L>::ReturnType>::invoke( lambda, temp );
4442  }
4443 
4444  template <typename L> struct BoundLambda : BoundValueRefBase {
4445  L m_lambda;
4446 
4447  static_assert(
4448  UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4449  "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4450  explicit BoundLambda( L const& lambda ): m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4451 
4452  auto setValue( std::string const& arg )
4453  -> ParserResult override {
4454  return invokeLambda<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType>(
4455  m_lambda, arg );
4456  }
4457  };
4458 
4459  template <typename L> struct BoundFlagLambda : BoundFlagRefBase {
4460  L m_lambda;
4461 
4462  static_assert(
4463  UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::isValid,
4464  "Supplied lambda must take exactly one argument" );
4465  static_assert(
4466  std::is_same<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<L>::ArgType,
4467  bool>::value,
4468  "flags must be boolean" );
4469 
4470  explicit BoundFlagLambda( L const& lambda ):
4471  m_lambda( lambda ) {}
4472 
4473  auto setFlag( bool flag ) -> ParserResult override {
4474  return LambdaInvoker<typename UnaryLambdaTraits<
4475  L>::ReturnType>::invoke( m_lambda, flag );
4476  }
4477  };

4479  enum class Optionality { Optional, Required };

4481  class ParserBase {
4482  public:
4483  virtual ~ParserBase() = default;
4484  virtual auto validate() const -> Result { return Result::ok(); }
4485  virtual auto parse( std::string const& exeName,
4486  TokenStream const& tokens ) const
4487  -> InternalParseResult = 0;
4488  virtual size_t cardinality() const;
4489 
4490  InternalParseResult parse( Args const& args ) const;
4491  };
4492 
4493  template <typename DerivedT>
4494  class ComposableParserImpl : public ParserBase {
4495  public:
4496  template <typename T>
4497  auto operator|( T const& other ) const -> Parser;
4498  };
4499 
4500  // Common code and state for Args and Opts
4501  template <typename DerivedT>
4502  class ParserRefImpl : public ComposableParserImpl<DerivedT> {
4503  protected:
4504  Optionality m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4505  std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> m_ref;
4506  std::string m_hint;
4507  std::string m_description;
4508 
4509  explicit ParserRefImpl( std::shared_ptr<BoundRef> const& ref ):
4510  m_ref( ref ) {}
4511 
4512  public:
4513  template <typename T>
4514  ParserRefImpl( T& ref, std::string const& hint ):
4515  m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundValueRef<T>>( ref ) ),
4516  m_hint( hint ) {}
4517 
4518  template <typename LambdaT>
4519  ParserRefImpl( LambdaT const& ref, std::string const& hint ):
4520  m_ref( std::make_shared<BoundLambda<LambdaT>>( ref ) ),
4521  m_hint( hint ) {}
4522 
4523  auto operator()( std::string const& description ) -> DerivedT& {
4524  m_description = description;
4525  return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4526  }
4527 
4528  auto optional() -> DerivedT& {
4529  m_optionality = Optionality::Optional;
4530  return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4531  }
4532 
4533  auto required() -> DerivedT& {
4534  m_optionality = Optionality::Required;
4535  return static_cast<DerivedT&>( *this );
4536  }
4537 
4538  auto isOptional() const -> bool {
4539  return m_optionality == Optionality::Optional;
4540  }
4541 
4542  auto cardinality() const -> size_t override {
4543  if ( m_ref->isContainer() )
4544  return 0;
4545  else
4546  return 1;
4547  }
4548 
4549  std::string const& hint() const { return m_hint; }
4550  };
4551 
4552  } // namespace detail

4884  struct ITransientExpression {
4885  auto isBinaryExpression() const -> bool { return m_isBinaryExpression; }
4886  auto getResult() const -> bool { return m_result; }
4887  virtual void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const = 0;
4888 
4889  ITransientExpression( bool isBinaryExpression, bool result )
4890  : m_isBinaryExpression( isBinaryExpression ),
4891  m_result( result )
4892  {}
4893 
4894  ITransientExpression() = default;
4895  ITransientExpression(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
4896  ITransientExpression& operator=(ITransientExpression const&) = default;
4897 
4898  // We don't actually need a virtual destructor, but many static analysers
4899  // complain if it's not here :-(
4900  virtual ~ITransientExpression(); // = default;
4901 
4902  bool m_isBinaryExpression;
4903  bool m_result;
4904  friend std::ostream& operator<<(std::ostream& out, ITransientExpression const& expr) {
4905  expr.streamReconstructedExpression(out);
4906  return out;
4907  }
4908  };
4909 
4910  void formatReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os, std::string const& lhs, StringRef op, std::string const& rhs );
4911 
4912  template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
4913  class BinaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
4914  LhsT m_lhs;
4915  StringRef m_op;
4916  RhsT m_rhs;
4917 
4918  void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
4919  formatReconstructedExpression
4920  ( os, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs ), m_op, Catch::Detail::stringify( m_rhs ) );
4921  }
4922 
4923  public:
4924  BinaryExpr( bool comparisonResult, LhsT lhs, StringRef op, RhsT rhs )
4925  : ITransientExpression{ true, comparisonResult },
4926  m_lhs( lhs ),
4927  m_op( op ),
4928  m_rhs( rhs )
4929  {}
4930 
4931  template<typename T>
4932  auto operator && ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4933  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4934  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4935  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4936  }
4937 
4938  template<typename T>
4939  auto operator || ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4940  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4941  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4942  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4943  }
4944 
4945  template<typename T>
4946  auto operator == ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4947  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4948  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4949  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4950  }
4951 
4952  template<typename T>
4953  auto operator != ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4954  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4955  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4956  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4957  }
4958 
4959  template<typename T>
4960  auto operator > ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4961  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4962  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4963  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4964  }
4965 
4966  template<typename T>
4967  auto operator < ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4968  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4969  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4970  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4971  }
4972 
4973  template<typename T>
4974  auto operator >= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4975  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4976  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4977  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4978  }
4979 
4980  template<typename T>
4981  auto operator <= ( T ) const -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
4982  static_assert(always_false<T>::value,
4983  "chained comparisons are not supported inside assertions, "
4984  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
4985  }
4986  };

4988  template<typename LhsT>
4989  class UnaryExpr : public ITransientExpression {
4990  LhsT m_lhs;
4991 
4992  void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
4993  os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_lhs );
4994  }
4995 
4996  public:
4997  explicit UnaryExpr( LhsT lhs )
4998  : ITransientExpression{ false, static_cast<bool>(lhs) },
4999  m_lhs( lhs )
5000  {}
5001  };

5003 
5004  // Specialised comparison functions to handle equality comparisons between ints and pointers (NULL deduces as an int)
5005  template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
5006  auto compareEqual( LhsT const& lhs, RhsT const& rhs ) -> bool { return static_cast<bool>(lhs == rhs); }
5007  template<typename T>
5008  auto compareEqual( T* const& lhs, int rhs ) -> bool { return lhs == reinterpret_cast<void const*>( rhs ); }
5009  template<typename T>
5010  auto compareEqual( T* const& lhs, long rhs ) -> bool { return lhs == reinterpret_cast<void const*>( rhs ); }
5011  template<typename T>
5012  auto compareEqual( int lhs, T* const& rhs ) -> bool { return reinterpret_cast<void const*>( lhs ) == rhs; }
5013  template<typename T>
5014  auto compareEqual( long lhs, T* const& rhs ) -> bool { return reinterpret_cast<void const*>( lhs ) == rhs; }
5015 
5016  template<typename LhsT, typename RhsT>
5017  auto compareNotEqual( LhsT const& lhs, RhsT&& rhs ) -> bool { return static_cast<bool>(lhs != rhs); }
5018  template<typename T>
5019  auto compareNotEqual( T* const& lhs, int rhs ) -> bool { return lhs != reinterpret_cast<void const*>( rhs ); }
5020  template<typename T>
5021  auto compareNotEqual( T* const& lhs, long rhs ) -> bool { return lhs != reinterpret_cast<void const*>( rhs ); }
5022  template<typename T>
5023  auto compareNotEqual( int lhs, T* const& rhs ) -> bool { return reinterpret_cast<void const*>( lhs ) != rhs; }
5024  template<typename T>
5025  auto compareNotEqual( long lhs, T* const& rhs ) -> bool { return reinterpret_cast<void const*>( lhs ) != rhs; }
5026 
5027 
5028  template<typename LhsT>
5029  class ExprLhs {
5030  LhsT m_lhs;
5031  public:
5032  explicit ExprLhs( LhsT lhs ) : m_lhs( lhs ) {}
5033 
5034  template<typename RhsT>
5035  auto operator == ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5036  return { compareEqual( m_lhs, rhs ), m_lhs, "=="_sr, rhs };
5037  }
5038  auto operator == ( bool rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, bool> const {
5039  return { m_lhs == rhs, m_lhs, "=="_sr, rhs };
5040  }
5041 
5042  template<typename RhsT>
5043  auto operator != ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5044  return { compareNotEqual( m_lhs, rhs ), m_lhs, "!="_sr, rhs };
5045  }
5046  auto operator != ( bool rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, bool> const {
5047  return { m_lhs != rhs, m_lhs, "!="_sr, rhs };
5048  }
5049 
5050  template<typename RhsT>
5051  auto operator > ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5052  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs > rhs), m_lhs, ">"_sr, rhs };
5053  }
5054  template<typename RhsT>
5055  auto operator < ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5056  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs < rhs), m_lhs, "<"_sr, rhs };
5057  }
5058  template<typename RhsT>
5059  auto operator >= ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5060  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs >= rhs), m_lhs, ">="_sr, rhs };
5061  }
5062  template<typename RhsT>
5063  auto operator <= ( RhsT const& rhs ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5064  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs <= rhs), m_lhs, "<="_sr, rhs };
5065  }
5066  template <typename RhsT>
5067  auto operator | (RhsT const& rhs) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5068  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs | rhs), m_lhs, "|"_sr, rhs };
5069  }
5070  template <typename RhsT>
5071  auto operator & (RhsT const& rhs) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5072  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs & rhs), m_lhs, "&"_sr, rhs };
5073  }
5074  template <typename RhsT>
5075  auto operator ^ (RhsT const& rhs) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5076  return { static_cast<bool>(m_lhs ^ rhs), m_lhs, "^"_sr, rhs };
5077  }
5078 
5079  template<typename RhsT>
5080  auto operator && ( RhsT const& ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5081  static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5082  "operator&& is not supported inside assertions, "
5083  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5084  }
5085 
5086  template<typename RhsT>
5087  auto operator || ( RhsT const& ) -> BinaryExpr<LhsT, RhsT const&> const {
5088  static_assert(always_false<RhsT>::value,
5089  "operator|| is not supported inside assertions, "
5090  "wrap the expression inside parentheses, or decompose it");
5091  }
5092 
5093  auto makeUnaryExpr() const -> UnaryExpr<LhsT> {
5094  return UnaryExpr<LhsT>{ m_lhs };
5095  }
5096  };
5097 
5098  void handleExpression( ITransientExpression const& expr );
5099 
5100  template<typename T>
5101  void handleExpression( ExprLhs<T> const& expr ) {
5102  handleExpression( expr.makeUnaryExpr() );
5103  }
5104 
5105  struct Decomposer {
5106  template<typename T>
5107  auto operator <= ( T const& lhs ) -> ExprLhs<T const&> {
5108  return ExprLhs<T const&>{ lhs };
5109  }
5110 
5111  auto operator <=( bool value ) -> ExprLhs<bool> {
5112  return ExprLhs<bool>{ value };
5113  }
5114  };

5187 // We need this suppression to leak, because it took until GCC 9
5188 // for the front end to handle local suppression via _Pragma properly

5192 
5193 #if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE)
5194 
5195 #if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION)
5196  #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) #__VA_ARGS__
5197 #else
5198  #define CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(...) "Disabled by CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_STRINGIFICATION"
5199 #endif
5200 
5201 #if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE) || defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
5202 
5204 // Another way to speed-up compilation is to omit local try-catch for REQUIRE*
5205 // macros.
5206 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY
5207 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( capturer )
5208 
5209 #else // CATCH_CONFIG_FAST_COMPILE
5210 
5211 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY try
5212 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( handler ) catch(...) { handler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); }
5213 
5214 #endif
5215 
5216 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( handler ) handler.complete();
5217 
5219 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5220  do { \
5221  /* The expression should not be evaluated, but warnings should hopefully be checked */ \
5222  CATCH_INTERNAL_IGNORE_BUT_WARN(__VA_ARGS__); \
5223  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5224  INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
5225  CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5226  CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_PARENTHESES_WARNINGS \
5227  catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::Decomposer() <= __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5228  CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5229  } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5230  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5231  } while( (void)0, (false) && static_cast<bool>( !!(__VA_ARGS__) ) )
5232 
5234 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_IF( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5235  INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5236  if( Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5237 
5239 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_ELSE( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5240  INTERNAL_CATCH_TEST( macroName, resultDisposition, __VA_ARGS__ ); \
5241  if( !Catch::getResultCapture().lastAssertionPassed() )
5242 
5244 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_NO_THROW( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5245  do { \
5246  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition ); \
5247  try { \
5248  static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5249  catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionNotThrownAsExpected(); \
5250  } \
5251  catch( ... ) { \
5252  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5253  } \
5254  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5255  } while( false )
5256 
5258 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS( macroName, resultDisposition, ... ) \
5259  do { \
5260  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__), resultDisposition); \
5261  if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5262  try { \
5263  static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5264  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5265  } \
5266  catch( ... ) { \
5267  catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5268  } \
5269  else \
5270  catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5271  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5272  } while( false )
5273 
5275 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_AS( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, expr ) \
5276  do { \
5277  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(expr) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType), resultDisposition ); \
5278  if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5279  try { \
5280  static_cast<void>(expr); \
5281  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5282  } \
5283  catch( exceptionType const& ) { \
5284  catchAssertionHandler.handleExceptionThrownAsExpected(); \
5285  } \
5286  catch( ... ) { \
5287  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
5288  } \
5289  else \
5290  catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5291  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5292  } while( false )
5293 
5294 
5295 
5297 // Although this is matcher-based, it can be used with just a string
5298 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_STR_MATCHES( macroName, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
5299  do { \
5300  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
5301  if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
5302  try { \
5303  static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__); \
5304  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
5305  } \
5306  catch( ... ) { \
5307  Catch::handleExceptionMatchExpr( catchAssertionHandler, matcher, #matcher##_catch_sr ); \
5308  } \
5309  else \
5310  catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
5311  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
5312  } while( false )
5313

5353 #define CATCH_REC_GET_END(...) CATCH_REC_GET_END1
5354 #define CATCH_REC_NEXT0(test, next, ...) next CATCH_REC_OUT
5355 #define CATCH_REC_NEXT1(test, next) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT0 ) ( test, next, 0)
