5362 #define CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
5363 #define CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) , f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST0_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
5364 #define CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, x, peek, ...) f(userdata, x) CATCH_DEFER ( CATCH_REC_NEXT(peek, CATCH_REC_LIST1_UD) ) ( f, userdata, peek, __VA_ARGS__ )
5365 
5366 // Applies the function macro `f` to each of the remaining parameters, inserts commas between the results,
5367 // and passes userdata as the first parameter to each invocation,
5368 // e.g. CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, x, a, b, c) evaluates to f(x, a), f(x, b), f(x, c)
5369 #define CATCH_REC_LIST_UD(f, userdata, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2_UD(f, userdata, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))
5370 
5371 #define CATCH_REC_LIST(f, ...) CATCH_RECURSE(CATCH_REC_LIST2(f, __VA_ARGS__, ()()(), ()()(), ()()(), 0))

5418 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN\
5419  template<typename...> struct TypeList {};\
5420  template<typename...Ts>\
5421  constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TypeList<Ts...> { return {}; }\
5422  template<template<typename...> class...> struct TemplateTypeList{};\
5423  template<template<typename...> class...Cs>\
5424  constexpr auto get_wrapper() noexcept -> TemplateTypeList<Cs...> { return {}; }\
5425  template<typename...>\
5426  struct append;\
5427  template<typename...>\
5428  struct rewrap;\
5429  template<template<typename...> class, typename...>\
5430  struct create;\
5431  template<template<typename...> class, typename>\
5432  struct convert;\
5433  \
5434  template<typename T> \
5435  struct append<T> { using type = T; };\
5436  template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, template<typename...> class L2, typename...E2, typename...Rest>\
5437  struct append<L1<E1...>, L2<E2...>, Rest...> { using type = typename append<L1<E1...,E2...>, Rest...>::type; };\
5438  template< template<typename...> class L1, typename...E1, typename...Rest>\
5439  struct append<L1<E1...>, TypeList<mpl_::na>, Rest...> { using type = L1<E1...>; };\
5440  \
5441  template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, typename...elems>\
5442  struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<elems...>> { using type = TypeList<Container<elems...>>; };\
5443  template< template<typename...> class Container, template<typename...> class List, class...Elems, typename...Elements>\
5444  struct rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, List<Elems...>, Elements...> { using type = typename append<TypeList<Container<Elems...>>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Container>, Elements...>::type>::type; };\
5445  \
5446  template<template <typename...> class Final, template< typename...> class...Containers, typename...Types>\
5447  struct create<Final, TemplateTypeList<Containers...>, TypeList<Types...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>, typename rewrap<TemplateTypeList<Containers>, Types...>::type...>::type; };\
5448  template<template <typename...> class Final, template <typename...> class List, typename...Ts>\
5449  struct convert<Final, List<Ts...>> { using type = typename append<Final<>,TypeList<Ts>...>::type; };

5662 // GCC 5 and older do not properly handle disabling unused-variable warning
5663 // with a _Pragma. This means that we have to leak the suppression to the
5664 // user code as well :-(
5665 #if defined(__GNUC__) && !defined(__clang__) && __GNUC__ <= 5
5666 #pragma GCC diagnostic ignored "-Wunused-variable"
5667 #endif

5671 namespace Catch {
5672 
5673 template<typename C>
5674 class TestInvokerAsMethod : public ITestInvoker {
5675  void (C::*m_testAsMethod)();
5676 public:
5677  TestInvokerAsMethod( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) noexcept : m_testAsMethod( testAsMethod ) {}
5678 
5679  void invoke() const override {
5680  C obj;
5681  (obj.*m_testAsMethod)();
5682  }
5683 };
5684 
5685 Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void(*testAsFunction)() );
5686 
5687 template<typename C>
5688 Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker> makeTestInvoker( void (C::*testAsMethod)() ) {
5689  return Detail::unique_ptr<ITestInvoker>( new TestInvokerAsMethod<C>(testAsMethod) );
5690 }

5692 struct NameAndTags {
5693  NameAndTags(StringRef const& name_ = StringRef(),
5694  StringRef const& tags_ = StringRef()) noexcept:
5695  name(name_), tags(tags_) {}
5696  StringRef name;
5697  StringRef tags;
5698 };

5723  namespace{ Catch::AutoReg INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( autoRegistrar )( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestName ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), Catch::NameAndTags{ __VA_ARGS__ } ); } /* NOLINT */ \

5742  void test(); \
5743  }; \

5745  } \

5757  CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
5758  } while(false)

6061  CATCH_INTERNAL_START_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6062  CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6063  CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \

6067  namespace {\
6068  namespace INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_NAMESPACE(TestName) { \
6069  INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN \
6070  INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_GEN(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature)) \
6071  template<typename... Types> \
6072  struct TestName { \
6073  void reg_tests() { \
6074  int index = 0; \
6075  using expander = int[]; \
6076  constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes))};\
6077  constexpr char const* types_list[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))};\
6078  constexpr auto num_types = sizeof(types_list) / sizeof(types_list[0]);\
6079  (void)expander{(Catch::AutoReg( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestFuncName<Types> ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, Catch::StringRef(), Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index / num_types]) + "<" + std::string(types_list[index % num_types]) + ">", Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */\
6080  } \
6081  }; \
6082  static int INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( globalRegistrar ) = [](){ \
6083  using TestInit = typename create<TestName, decltype(get_wrapper<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes)>()), TypeList<INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_TYPE_LISTS_FROM_TYPES(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))>>::type; \
6084  TestInit t; \
6085  t.reg_tests(); \
6086  return 0; \
6087  }(); \
6088  } \
6089  } \

6190  CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_GLOBALS_WARNINGS \
6191  CATCH_INTERNAL_SUPPRESS_ZERO_VARIADIC_WARNINGS \

6194  template<typename TestType> \
6195  struct TestName : INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(ClassName <TestType>) { \
6196  void test();\
6197  };\
6198  namespace {\
6199  namespace INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_NAMESPACE(TestNameClass) {\
6200  INTERNAL_CATCH_TYPE_GEN \
6201  INTERNAL_CATCH_NTTP_GEN(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(Signature))\
6202  template<typename...Types>\
6203  struct TestNameClass{\
6204  void reg_tests(){\
6205  int index = 0;\
6206  using expander = int[];\
6207  constexpr char const* tmpl_types[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes))};\
6208  constexpr char const* types_list[] = {CATCH_REC_LIST(INTERNAL_CATCH_STRINGIZE_WITHOUT_PARENS, INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))};\
6209  constexpr auto num_types = sizeof(types_list) / sizeof(types_list[0]);\
6210  (void)expander{(Catch::AutoReg( Catch::makeTestInvoker( &TestName<Types>::test ), CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, #ClassName, Catch::NameAndTags{ Name " - " + std::string(tmpl_types[index / num_types]) + "<" + std::string(types_list[index % num_types]) + ">", Tags } ), index++)... };/* NOLINT */ \
6211  }\
6212  };\
6213  static int INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( globalRegistrar ) = [](){\
6214  using TestInit = typename create<TestNameClass, decltype(get_wrapper<INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TmplTypes)>()), TypeList<INTERNAL_CATCH_MAKE_TYPE_LISTS_FROM_TYPES(INTERNAL_CATCH_REMOVE_PARENS(TypesList))>>::type;\
6215  TestInit t;\
6216  t.reg_tests();\
6217  return 0;\
6218  }(); \
6219  }\
6220  }\

6407  IsHidden = 1 << 1,
6408  ShouldFail = 1 << 2,
6409  MayFail = 1 << 3,
6410  Throws = 1 << 4,
6411  NonPortable = 1 << 5,
6412  Benchmark = 1 << 6
6413  };

6419  NameAndTags const& _tags,
6420  SourceLineInfo const& _lineInfo);

6432

6434  std::string className;
6435  private:

6437  // Internally we copy tags to the backing storage and then add
6438  // refs to this storage to the tags vector.

6440  public:
6441  std::vector<Tag> tags;
6442  SourceLineInfo lineInfo;

6455  }

6512  class ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar {
6513  template<typename T>
6514  class ExceptionTranslator : public IExceptionTranslator {
6515  public:
6516 
6517  ExceptionTranslator( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) )
6518  : m_translateFunction( translateFunction )
6519  {}
6520 
6521  std::string translate( ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator it, ExceptionTranslators::const_iterator itEnd ) const override {
6522 #if !defined(CATCH_CONFIG_DISABLE_EXCEPTIONS)
6523  try {
6524  if( it == itEnd )
6525  std::rethrow_exception(std::current_exception());
6526  else
6527  return (*it)->translate( it+1, itEnd );
6528  }
6529  catch( T const& ex ) {
6530  return m_translateFunction( ex );
6531  }
6532 #else
6533  return "You should never get here!";
6534 #endif
6535  }
6536 
6537  protected:
6538  std::string(*m_translateFunction)( T const& );
6539  };
6540 
6541  public:
6542  template<typename T>
6543  ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar( std::string(*translateFunction)( T const& ) ) {
6544  getMutableRegistryHub().registerTranslator
6545  ( new ExceptionTranslator<T>( translateFunction ) );
6546  }
6547  };
6548 
6549 } // namespace Catch

6556  namespace{ Catch::ExceptionTranslatorRegistrar INTERNAL_CATCH_UNIQUE_NAME( catch_internal_ExceptionRegistrar )( &translatorName ); } \
6557  CATCH_INTERNAL_STOP_WARNINGS_SUPPRESSION \
6558  static std::string translatorName( signature )

6678  class GeneratorUntypedBase {
6679  public:
6680  GeneratorUntypedBase() = default;
6681  // Generation of copy ops is deprecated (and Clang will complain)
6682  // if there is a user destructor defined
6683  GeneratorUntypedBase(GeneratorUntypedBase const&) = default;
6684  GeneratorUntypedBase& operator=(GeneratorUntypedBase const&) = default;
6685 
6686  virtual ~GeneratorUntypedBase(); // = default;
6687 
6688  // Attempts to move the generator to the next element
6689  //
6690  // Returns true iff the move succeeded (and a valid element
6691  // can be retrieved).
6692  virtual bool next() = 0;
6693  };
6694  using GeneratorBasePtr = Catch::Detail::unique_ptr<GeneratorUntypedBase>;
6695 
6696  } // namespace Generators

6702  virtual void setGenerator( Generators::GeneratorBasePtr&& generator ) = 0;

6725  template<typename T>
6726  struct IGenerator : GeneratorUntypedBase {
6727  ~IGenerator() override = default;
6728  IGenerator() = default;
6729  IGenerator(IGenerator const&) = default;
6730  IGenerator& operator=(IGenerator const&) = default;
6731 
6732 
6733  // Returns the current element of the generator
6734  //
6735  // \Precondition The generator is either freshly constructed,
6736  // or the last call to `next()` returned true
6737  virtual T const& get() const = 0;
6738  using type = T;
6739  };

6744  template <typename T>

6746  GeneratorPtr<T> m_generator;
6747  public:
6749  GeneratorWrapper(IGenerator<T>* generator):
6750  m_generator(generator) {}
6751  GeneratorWrapper(GeneratorPtr<T> generator):
6752  m_generator(std::move(generator)) {}
6753 
6754  T const& get() const {
6755  return m_generator->get();
6756  }
6757  bool next() {
6758  return m_generator->next();
6759  }
6760  };

6779  template<typename T>
6780  class FixedValuesGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
6781  static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
6782  "FixedValuesGenerator does not support bools because of std::vector<bool>"
6783  "specialization, use SingleValue Generator instead.");

6785  size_t m_idx = 0;
6786  public:
6787  FixedValuesGenerator( std::initializer_list<T> values ) : m_values( values ) {}
6788 
6789  T const& get() const override {
6790  return m_values[m_idx];
6791  }

6807  template<typename T>
6808  class Generators : public IGenerator<T> {
6809  std::vector<GeneratorWrapper<T>> m_generators;
6810  size_t m_current = 0;
6811 
6812  void populate(GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
6813  m_generators.emplace_back(std::move(generator));
6814  }
6815  void populate(T&& val) {
6816  m_generators.emplace_back(value(std::forward<T>(val)));
6817  }
6818  template<typename U>
6819  void populate(U&& val) {
6820  populate(T(std::forward<U>(val)));
6821  }
6822  template<typename U, typename... Gs>
6823  void populate(U&& valueOrGenerator, Gs &&... moreGenerators) {
6824  populate(std::forward<U>(valueOrGenerator));
6825  populate(std::forward<Gs>(moreGenerators)...);
6826  }
6827 
6828  public:
6829  template <typename... Gs>
6830  Generators(Gs &&... moreGenerators) {
6831  m_generators.reserve(sizeof...(Gs));
6832  populate(std::forward<Gs>(moreGenerators)...);
6833  }
6834 
6835  T const& get() const override {
6836  return m_generators[m_current].get();
6837  }
6838 
6839  bool next() override {
6840  if (m_current >= m_generators.size()) {
6841  return false;
6842  }
6843  const bool current_status = m_generators[m_current].next();
6844  if (!current_status) {
6845  ++m_current;
6846  }
6847  return m_current < m_generators.size();
6848  }
6849  };
6850

6854  return values<std::tuple<Ts...>>( tuples );
6855  }

6861  template<typename T, typename... Gs>
6862  auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
6863  return Generators<T>(std::move(generator), std::forward<Gs>(moreGenerators)...);
6864  }
6865  template<typename T>
6866  auto makeGenerators( GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator ) -> Generators<T> {
6867  return Generators<T>(std::move(generator));
6868  }
6869  template<typename T, typename... Gs>
6870  auto makeGenerators( T&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
6871  return makeGenerators( value( std::forward<T>( val ) ), std::forward<Gs>( moreGenerators )... );
6872  }
6873  template<typename T, typename U, typename... Gs>
6874  auto makeGenerators( as<T>, U&& val, Gs &&... moreGenerators ) -> Generators<T> {
6875  return makeGenerators( value( T( std::forward<U>( val ) ) ), std::forward<Gs>( moreGenerators )... );
6876  }
6877 
6878  auto acquireGeneratorTracker( StringRef generatorName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo ) -> IGeneratorTracker&;
6879 
6880  template<typename L>
6881  // Note: The type after -> is weird, because VS2015 cannot parse
6882  // the expression used in the typedef inside, when it is in
6883  // return type. Yeah.
6884  auto generate( StringRef generatorName, SourceLineInfo const& lineInfo, L const& generatorExpression ) -> decltype(std::declval<decltype(generatorExpression())>().get()) {
6885  using UnderlyingType = typename decltype(generatorExpression())::type;
6886 
6887  IGeneratorTracker& tracker = acquireGeneratorTracker( generatorName, lineInfo );
6888  if (!tracker.hasGenerator()) {
6889  tracker.setGenerator(Catch::Detail::make_unique<Generators<UnderlyingType>>(generatorExpression()));
6890  }
6891 
6892  auto const& generator = static_cast<IGenerator<UnderlyingType> const&>( *tracker.getGenerator() );
6893  return generator.get();
6894  }

6922  template <typename T>
6923  class TakeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
6924  GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
6925  size_t m_returned = 0;
6926  size_t m_target;
6927  public:
6928  TakeGenerator(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
6929  m_generator(std::move(generator)),
6930  m_target(target)
6931  {
6932  assert(target != 0 && "Empty generators are not allowed");
6933  }
6934  T const& get() const override {
6935  return m_generator.get();
6936  }
6937  bool next() override {
6938  ++m_returned;
6939  if (m_returned >= m_target) {
6940  return false;
6941  }
6942 
6943  const auto success = m_generator.next();
6944  // If the underlying generator does not contain enough values
6945  // then we cut short as well
6946  if (!success) {
6947  m_returned = m_target;
6948  }
6949  return success;
6950  }
6951  };
6952 
6953  template <typename T>
6954  GeneratorWrapper<T> take(size_t target, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
6955  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<TakeGenerator<T>>(target, std::move(generator)));
6956  }

6958 
6959  template <typename T, typename Predicate>
6960  class FilterGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
6961  GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
6962  Predicate m_predicate;
6963  public:
6964  template <typename P = Predicate>
6965  FilterGenerator(P&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
6966  m_generator(std::move(generator)),
6967  m_predicate(std::forward<P>(pred))
6968  {
6969  if (!m_predicate(m_generator.get())) {
6970  // It might happen that there are no values that pass the
6971  // filter. In that case we throw an exception.
6972  auto has_initial_value = next();
6973  if (!has_initial_value) {
6974  Detail::throw_generator_exception("No valid value found in filtered generator");
6975  }
6976  }
6977  }
6978 
6979  T const& get() const override {
6980  return m_generator.get();
6981  }
6982 
6983  bool next() override {
6984  bool success = m_generator.next();
6985  if (!success) {
6986  return false;
6987  }
6988  while (!m_predicate(m_generator.get()) && (success = m_generator.next()) == true);
6989  return success;
6990  }
6991  };
6992 
6993 
6994  template <typename T, typename Predicate>
6995  GeneratorWrapper<T> filter(Predicate&& pred, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
6996  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<FilterGenerator<T, Predicate>>(std::forward<Predicate>(pred), std::move(generator)));
6997  }
6998 
6999  template <typename T>
7000  class RepeatGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7001  static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7002  "RepeatGenerator currently does not support bools"
7003  "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
7004  GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7005  mutable std::vector<T> m_returned;
7006  size_t m_target_repeats;
7007  size_t m_current_repeat = 0;
7008  size_t m_repeat_index = 0;
7009  public:
7010  RepeatGenerator(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator):
7011  m_generator(std::move(generator)),
7012  m_target_repeats(repeats)
7013  {
7014  assert(m_target_repeats > 0 && "Repeat generator must repeat at least once");
7015  }
7016 
7017  T const& get() const override {
7018  if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7019  m_returned.push_back(m_generator.get());
7020  return m_returned.back();
7021  }
7022  return m_returned[m_repeat_index];
7023  }
7024 
7025  bool next() override {
7026  // There are 2 basic cases:
7027  // 1) We are still reading the generator
7028  // 2) We are reading our own cache
7029 
7030  // In the first case, we need to poke the underlying generator.
7031  // If it happily moves, we are left in that state, otherwise it is time to start reading from our cache
7032  if (m_current_repeat == 0) {
7033  const auto success = m_generator.next();
7034  if (!success) {
7035  ++m_current_repeat;
7036  }
7037  return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7038  }
7039 
7040  // In the second case, we need to move indices forward and check that we haven't run up against the end
7041  ++m_repeat_index;
7042  if (m_repeat_index == m_returned.size()) {
7043  m_repeat_index = 0;
7044  ++m_current_repeat;
7045  }
7046  return m_current_repeat < m_target_repeats;
7047  }
7048  };
7049 
7050  template <typename T>
7051  GeneratorWrapper<T> repeat(size_t repeats, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7052  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RepeatGenerator<T>>(repeats, std::move(generator)));
7053  }

7055  template <typename T, typename U, typename Func>
7056  class MapGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7057  // TBD: provide static assert for mapping function, for friendly error message
7058  GeneratorWrapper<U> m_generator;
7059  Func m_function;
7060  // To avoid returning dangling reference, we have to save the values
7061  T m_cache;
7062  public:
7063  template <typename F2 = Func>
7064  MapGenerator(F2&& function, GeneratorWrapper<U>&& generator) :
7065  m_generator(std::move(generator)),
7066  m_function(std::forward<F2>(function)),
7067  m_cache(m_function(m_generator.get()))
7068  {}
7069 
7070  T const& get() const override {
7071  return m_cache;
7072  }
7073  bool next() override {
7074  const auto success = m_generator.next();
7075  if (success) {
7076  m_cache = m_function(m_generator.get());
7077  }
7078  return success;
7079  }
7080  };

7092  Catch::Detail::make_unique<MapGenerator<T, U, Func>>(std::forward<Func>(function), std::move(generator))
7093  );

7096  template <typename T>
7097  class ChunkGenerator final : public IGenerator<std::vector<T>> {
7098  std::vector<T> m_chunk;
7099  size_t m_chunk_size;
7100  GeneratorWrapper<T> m_generator;
7101  bool m_used_up = false;
7102  public:
7103  ChunkGenerator(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T> generator) :
7104  m_chunk_size(size), m_generator(std::move(generator))
7105  {
7106  m_chunk.reserve(m_chunk_size);
7107  if (m_chunk_size != 0) {
7108  m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7109  for (size_t i = 1; i < m_chunk_size; ++i) {
7110  if (!m_generator.next()) {
7111  Detail::throw_generator_exception("Not enough values to initialize the first chunk");
7112  }
7113  m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7114  }
7115  }
7116  }
7117  std::vector<T> const& get() const override {
7118  return m_chunk;
7119  }
7120  bool next() override {
7121  m_chunk.clear();
7122  for (size_t idx = 0; idx < m_chunk_size; ++idx) {
7123  if (!m_generator.next()) {
7124  return false;
7125  }
7126  m_chunk.push_back(m_generator.get());
7127  }
7128  return true;
7129  }
7130  };
7131 
7132  template <typename T>
7133  GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>> chunk(size_t size, GeneratorWrapper<T>&& generator) {
7134  return GeneratorWrapper<std::vector<T>>(
7135  Catch::Detail::make_unique<ChunkGenerator<T>>(size, std::move(generator))
7136  );
7137  }

7157 
7158  // This is a simple implementation of C++11 Uniform Random Number
7159  // Generator. It does not provide all operators, because Catch2
7160  // does not use it, but it should behave as expected inside stdlib's
7161  // distributions.
7162  // The implementation is based on the PCG family (http://pcg-random.org)
7163  class SimplePcg32 {
7164  using state_type = std::uint64_t;
7165  public:
7166  using result_type = std::uint32_t;
7167  static constexpr result_type (min)() {
7168  return 0;
7169  }
7170  static constexpr result_type (max)() {
7171  return static_cast<result_type>(-1);
7172  }
7173 
7174  // Provide some default initial state for the default constructor
7175  SimplePcg32():SimplePcg32(0xed743cc4U) {}
7176 
7177  explicit SimplePcg32(result_type seed_);
7178 
7179  void seed(result_type seed_);
7180  void discard(uint64_t skip);
7181 
7182  result_type operator()();
7183 
7184  private:
7185  friend bool operator==(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
7186  friend bool operator!=(SimplePcg32 const& lhs, SimplePcg32 const& rhs);
7187 
7188  // In theory we also need operator<< and operator>>
7189  // In practice we do not use them, so we will skip them for now
7190 
7191 
7192  std::uint64_t m_state;
7193  // This part of the state determines which "stream" of the numbers
7194  // is chosen -- we take it as a constant for Catch2, so we only
7195  // need to deal with seeding the main state.
7196  // Picked by reading 8 bytes from `/dev/random` :-)
7197  static const std::uint64_t s_inc = (0x13ed0cc53f939476ULL << 1ULL) | 1ULL;
7198  };
7199 
7200 } // end namespace Catch
7201 
7202 #endif // CATCH_RANDOM_NUMBER_GENERATOR_HPP_INCLUDED
7203 
7204 #include <random>
7205 
7206 namespace Catch {
7207 namespace Generators {
7208 
7209 template <typename Float>
7210 class RandomFloatingGenerator final : public IGenerator<Float> {
7211  Catch::SimplePcg32& m_rng;
7212  std::uniform_real_distribution<Float> m_dist;
7213  Float m_current_number;
7214 public:
7215 
7216  RandomFloatingGenerator(Float a, Float b):
7217  m_rng(rng()),
7218  m_dist(a, b) {
7219  static_cast<void>(next());
7220  }
7221 
7222  Float const& get() const override {
7223  return m_current_number;
7224  }
7225  bool next() override {
7226  m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
7227  return true;
7228  }
7229 };
7230 
7231 template <typename Integer>
7232 class RandomIntegerGenerator final : public IGenerator<Integer> {
7233  Catch::SimplePcg32& m_rng;
7234  std::uniform_int_distribution<Integer> m_dist;
7235  Integer m_current_number;
7236 public:
7237 
7238  RandomIntegerGenerator(Integer a, Integer b):
7239  m_rng(rng()),
7240  m_dist(a, b) {
7241  static_cast<void>(next());
7242  }
7243 
7244  Integer const& get() const override {
7245  return m_current_number;
7246  }
7247  bool next() override {
7248  m_current_number = m_dist(m_rng);
7249  return true;
7250  }
7251 };
7252 
7253 // TODO: Ideally this would be also constrained against the various char types,
7254 // but I don't expect users to run into that in practice.
7255 template <typename T>
7256 std::enable_if_t<std::is_integral<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7257 GeneratorWrapper<T>>
7258 random(T a, T b) {
7259  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7260  Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomIntegerGenerator<T>>(a, b)
7261  );
7262 }
7263 
7264 template <typename T>
7265 std::enable_if_t<std::is_floating_point<T>::value,
7266 GeneratorWrapper<T>>
7267 random(T a, T b) {
7268  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(
7269  Catch::Detail::make_unique<RandomFloatingGenerator<T>>(a, b)
7270  );
7271 }

7285 #include <iterator>

7287 
7288 namespace Catch {
7289 namespace Generators {
7290 
7291 
7292 template <typename T>
7293 class RangeGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7294  T m_current;
7295  T m_end;
7296  T m_step;
7297  bool m_positive;
7298 
7299 public:
7300  RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step):
7301  m_current(start),
7302  m_end(end),
7303  m_step(step),
7304  m_positive(m_step > T(0))
7305  {
7306  assert(m_current != m_end && "Range start and end cannot be equal");
7307  assert(m_step != T(0) && "Step size cannot be zero");
7308  assert(((m_positive && m_current <= m_end) || (!m_positive && m_current >= m_end)) && "Step moves away from end");
7309  }
7310 
7311  RangeGenerator(T const& start, T const& end):
7312  RangeGenerator(start, end, (start < end) ? T(1) : T(-1))
7313  {}
7314 
7315  T const& get() const override {
7316  return m_current;
7317  }
7318 
7319  bool next() override {
7320  m_current += m_step;
7321  return (m_positive) ? (m_current < m_end) : (m_current > m_end);
7322  }
7323 };
7324 
7325 template <typename T>
7326 GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end, T const& step) {
7327  static_assert(std::is_arithmetic<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be numeric");
7328  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end, step));
7329 }
7330 
7331 template <typename T>
7332 GeneratorWrapper<T> range(T const& start, T const& end) {
7333  static_assert(std::is_integral<T>::value && !std::is_same<T, bool>::value, "Type must be an integer");
7334  return GeneratorWrapper<T>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<RangeGenerator<T>>(start, end));
7335 }
7336 
7337 
7338 template <typename T>
7339 class IteratorGenerator final : public IGenerator<T> {
7340  static_assert(!std::is_same<T, bool>::value,
7341  "IteratorGenerator currently does not support bools"
7342  "because of std::vector<bool> specialization");
7343 
7344  std::vector<T> m_elems;
7345  size_t m_current = 0;
7346 public:
7347  template <typename InputIterator, typename InputSentinel>
7348  IteratorGenerator(InputIterator first, InputSentinel last):m_elems(first, last) {
7349  if (m_elems.empty()) {
7350  Detail::throw_generator_exception("IteratorGenerator received no valid values");
7351  }
7352  }
7353 
7354  T const& get() const override {
7355  return m_elems[m_current];
7356  }
7357 
7358  bool next() override {
7359  ++m_current;
7360  return m_current != m_elems.size();
7361  }
7362 };
7363 
7364 template <typename InputIterator,
7365  typename InputSentinel,
7366  typename ResultType = typename std::iterator_traits<InputIterator>::value_type>
7367 GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(InputIterator from, InputSentinel to) {
7368  return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(from, to));
7369 }
7370 
7371 template <typename Container,
7372  typename ResultType = typename Container::value_type>
7373 GeneratorWrapper<ResultType> from_range(Container const& cnt) {
7374  return GeneratorWrapper<ResultType>(Catch::Detail::make_unique<IteratorGenerator<ResultType>>(cnt.begin(), cnt.end()));
7375 }
7376 
7377 
7378 } // namespace Generators

7589 #ifndef CATCH_CONTAINER_NONMEMBERS_HPP_INCLUDED
7590 #define CATCH_CONTAINER_NONMEMBERS_HPP_INCLUDED

7592 
7593 
7594 // We want a simple polyfill over `std::empty`, `std::size` and so on
7595 // for C++14 or C++ libraries with incomplete support.
7596 // We also have to handle that MSVC std lib will happily provide these
7597 // under older standards.
7598 #if defined(CATCH_CPP17_OR_GREATER) || defined(_MSC_VER)
7599 
7600 // We are already using this header either way, so there shouldn't
7601 // be much additional overhead in including it to get the feature
7602 // test macros
7603 #include <string>
7604 
7605 # if !defined(__cpp_lib_nonmember_container_access)
7606 # define CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
7607 # endif
7608 
7609 #else
7610 #define CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
7611 #endif
7612 
7613 
7614 
7615 namespace Catch {
7616 namespace Detail {
7617 
7618 #if defined(CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS)
7619  template <typename Container>
7620  constexpr auto empty(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.empty()) {
7621  return cont.empty();
7622  }
7623  template <typename T, std::size_t N>
7624  constexpr bool empty(const T (&)[N]) noexcept {
7625  // GCC < 7 does not support the const T(&)[] parameter syntax
7626  // so we have to ignore the length explicitly
7627  (void)N;
7628  return false;
7629  }
7630  template <typename T>
7631  constexpr bool empty(std::initializer_list<T> list) noexcept {
7632  return list.size() > 0;
7633  }
7634 
7635 
7636  template <typename Container>
7637  constexpr auto size(Container const& cont) -> decltype(cont.size()) {
7638  return cont.size();
7639  }
7640  template <typename T, std::size_t N>
7641  constexpr std::size_t size(const T(&)[N]) noexcept {
7642  return N;
7643  }
7644 #endif // CATCH_CONFIG_POLYFILL_NONMEMBER_CONTAINER_ACCESS
7645 
7646 } // end namespace Detail
7647 } // end namespace Catch

7671  bool isDebuggerActive();
7672 }
7673 
7674 #ifdef CATCH_PLATFORM_MAC
7675 
7676  #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
7677  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3\n" : : ) /* NOLINT */
7678  #elif defined(__aarch64__)
7679  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd4200000")
7680  #endif
7681 
7682 #elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_IPHONE)
7683 
7684  // use inline assembler
7685  #if defined(__i386__) || defined(__x86_64__)
7686  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__("int $3")
7687  #elif defined(__aarch64__)
7688  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xd4200000")
7689  #elif defined(__arm__) && !defined(__thumb__)
7690  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xe7f001f0")
7691  #elif defined(__arm__) && defined(__thumb__)
7692  #define CATCH_TRAP() __asm__(".inst 0xde01")
7693  #endif
7694 
7695 #elif defined(CATCH_PLATFORM_LINUX)
7696  // If we can use inline assembler, do it because this allows us to break
7697  // directly at the location of the failing check instead of breaking inside
7698  // raise() called from it, i.e. one stack frame below.
7699  #if defined(__GNUC__) && (defined(__i386) || defined(__x86_64))
7700  #define CATCH_TRAP() asm volatile ("int $3") /* NOLINT */
7701  #else // Fall back to the generic way.
7702  #include <signal.h>
7703 
7704  #define CATCH_TRAP() raise(SIGTRAP)
7705  #endif
7706 #elif defined(_MSC_VER)
7707  #define CATCH_TRAP() __debugbreak()
7708 #elif defined(__MINGW32__)
7709  extern "C" __declspec(dllimport) void __stdcall DebugBreak();
7710  #define CATCH_TRAP() DebugBreak()
7711 #endif
7712 
7713 #ifndef CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER
7714  #ifdef CATCH_TRAP
7715  #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{ if( Catch::isDebuggerActive() ) { CATCH_TRAP(); } }()
7716  #else
7717  #define CATCH_BREAK_INTO_DEBUGGER() []{}()
7718  #endif
7719 #endif
7720 
7721 #endif // CATCH_DEBUGGER_HPP_INCLUDED

7935 #ifndef CATCH_OPTION_HPP_INCLUDED
7936 #define CATCH_OPTION_HPP_INCLUDED
7937 
7938 namespace Catch {
7939 
7940  // An optional type
7941  template<typename T>
7942  class Option {
7943  public:
7944  Option() : nullableValue( nullptr ) {}
7945  Option( T const& _value )
7946  : nullableValue( new( storage ) T( _value ) )
7947  {}
7948  Option( Option const& _other )
7949  : nullableValue( _other ? new( storage ) T( *_other ) : nullptr )
7950  {}
7951 
7952  ~Option() {
7953  reset();
7954  }
7955 
7956  Option& operator= ( Option const& _other ) {
7957  if( &_other != this ) {
7958  reset();
7959  if( _other )
7960  nullableValue = new( storage ) T( *_other );
7961  }
7962  return *this;
7963  }
7964  Option& operator = ( T const& _value ) {
7965  reset();
7966  nullableValue = new( storage ) T( _value );
7967  return *this;
7968  }
7969 
7970  void reset() {
7971  if( nullableValue )
7972  nullableValue->~T();
7973  nullableValue = nullptr;
7974  }
7975 
7976  T& operator*() { return *nullableValue; }
7977  T const& operator*() const { return *nullableValue; }
7978  T* operator->() { return nullableValue; }
7979  const T* operator->() const { return nullableValue; }
7980 
7981  T valueOr( T const& defaultValue ) const {
7982  return nullableValue ? *nullableValue : defaultValue;
7983  }
7984 
7985  bool some() const { return nullableValue != nullptr; }
7986  bool none() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
7987 
7988  bool operator !() const { return nullableValue == nullptr; }
7989  explicit operator bool() const {
7990  return some();
7991  }
7992 
7993  private:
7994  T *nullableValue;
7995  alignas(alignof(T)) char storage[sizeof(T)];
7996  };
7997 
7998 } // end namespace Catch
7999 
8000 #endif // CATCH_OPTION_HPP_INCLUDED

8082  #endif
8083  };

8474 
8475  struct ISingleton {
8476  virtual ~ISingleton();
8477  };
8478 
8479 
8480  void addSingleton( ISingleton* singleton );
8481  void cleanupSingletons();
8482 
8483 
8484  template<typename SingletonImplT, typename InterfaceT = SingletonImplT, typename MutableInterfaceT = InterfaceT>
8485  class Singleton : SingletonImplT, public ISingleton {
8486 
8487  static auto getInternal() -> Singleton* {
8488  static Singleton* s_instance = nullptr;
8489  if( !s_instance ) {
8490  s_instance = new Singleton;
8491  addSingleton( s_instance );
8492  }
8493  return s_instance;
8494  }
8495 
8496  public:
8497  static auto get() -> InterfaceT const& {
8498  return *getInternal();
8499  }
8500  static auto getMutable() -> MutableInterfaceT& {
8501  return *getInternal();
8502  }
8503  };
8504 
8505 } // namespace Catch

9062  template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
9063  class MatchExpr : public ITransientExpression {
9064  ArgT && m_arg;
9065  MatcherT const& m_matcher;
9066  StringRef m_matcherString;
9067  public:
9068  MatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher, StringRef const& matcherString )
9069  : ITransientExpression{ true, matcher.match( arg ) }, // not forwarding arg here on purpose
9070  m_arg( std::forward<ArgT>(arg) ),
9071  m_matcher( matcher ),
9072  m_matcherString( matcherString )
9073  {}
9074 
9075  void streamReconstructedExpression( std::ostream &os ) const override {
9076  auto matcherAsString = m_matcher.toString();
9077  os << Catch::Detail::stringify( m_arg ) << ' ';
9078  if( matcherAsString == Detail::unprintableString )
9079  os << m_matcherString;
9080  else
9081  os << matcherAsString;
9082  }
9083  };
9084 
9085  namespace Matchers {
9086  template <typename ArgT>
9087  struct MatcherBase;
9088  }
9089 
9090  using StringMatcher = Matchers::MatcherBase<std::string>;
9091 
9092  void handleExceptionMatchExpr( AssertionHandler& handler, StringMatcher const& matcher, StringRef const& matcherString );
9093 
9094  template<typename ArgT, typename MatcherT>
9095  auto makeMatchExpr( ArgT && arg, MatcherT const& matcher, StringRef const& matcherString ) -> MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT> {
9096  return MatchExpr<ArgT, MatcherT>( std::forward<ArgT>(arg), matcher, matcherString );
9097  }

9103 #define INTERNAL_CHECK_THAT( macroName, matcher, resultDisposition, arg ) \
9104  do { \
9105  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(arg) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
9106  INTERNAL_CATCH_TRY { \
9107  catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( arg, matcher, #matcher##_catch_sr ) ); \
9108  } INTERNAL_CATCH_CATCH( catchAssertionHandler ) \
9109  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
9110  } while( false )
9111 
9112 
9114 #define INTERNAL_CATCH_THROWS_MATCHES( macroName, exceptionType, resultDisposition, matcher, ... ) \
9115  do { \
9116  Catch::AssertionHandler catchAssertionHandler( macroName##_catch_sr, CATCH_INTERNAL_LINEINFO, CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(__VA_ARGS__) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(exceptionType) ", " CATCH_INTERNAL_STRINGIFY(matcher), resultDisposition ); \
9117  if( catchAssertionHandler.allowThrows() ) \
9118  try { \
9119  static_cast<void>(__VA_ARGS__ ); \
9120  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedExceptionNotThrown(); \
9121  } \
9122  catch( exceptionType const& ex ) { \
9123  catchAssertionHandler.handleExpr( Catch::makeMatchExpr( ex, matcher, #matcher##_catch_sr ) ); \
9124  } \
9125  catch( ... ) { \
9126  catchAssertionHandler.handleUnexpectedInflightException(); \
9127  } \
9128  else \
9129  catchAssertionHandler.handleThrowingCallSkipped(); \
9130  INTERNAL_CATCH_REACT( catchAssertionHandler ) \
9131  } while( false )
9132 
9133 
9134 #endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_IMPL_HPP_INCLUDED

9174  template<typename T>
9175  struct MatcherBase : MatcherUntypedBase, MatcherMethod<T> {};
9176 
9177  namespace Detail {
9178 
9179  template<typename ArgT>
9180  struct MatchAllOf final : MatcherBase<ArgT> {
9181  MatchAllOf() = default;
9182  MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
9183  MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf const&) = delete;
9184  MatchAllOf(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
9185  MatchAllOf& operator=(MatchAllOf&&) = default;
9186 
9187 
9188  bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
9189  for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
9190  if (!matcher->match(arg))
9191  return false;
9192  }
9193  return true;
9194  }
9195  std::string describe() const override {
9196  std::string description;
9197  description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
9198  description += "( ";
9199  bool first = true;
9200  for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
9201  if( first )
9202  first = false;
9203  else
9204  description += " and ";
9205  description += matcher->toString();
9206  }
9207  description += " )";
9208  return description;
9209  }
9210 
9211  friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatchAllOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
9212  lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
9213  return std::move(lhs);
9214  }
9215  friend MatchAllOf operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf&& rhs) {
9216  rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
9217  return std::move(rhs);
9218  }
9219 
9220  private:
9221  std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
9222  };
9223 
9226  template<typename ArgT>
9227  MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
9230  template<typename ArgT>
9231  MatchAllOf<ArgT> operator&& (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAllOf<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;
9232 
9233  template<typename ArgT>
9234  struct MatchAnyOf final : MatcherBase<ArgT> {
9235  MatchAnyOf() = default;
9236  MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
9237  MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf const&) = delete;
9238  MatchAnyOf(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
9239  MatchAnyOf& operator=(MatchAnyOf&&) = default;
9240 
9241  bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
9242  for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
9243  if (matcher->match(arg))
9244  return true;
9245  }
9246  return false;
9247  }
9248  std::string describe() const override {
9249  std::string description;
9250  description.reserve( 4 + m_matchers.size()*32 );
9251  description += "( ";
9252  bool first = true;
9253  for( auto matcher : m_matchers ) {
9254  if( first )
9255  first = false;
9256  else
9257  description += " or ";
9258  description += matcher->toString();
9259  }
9260  description += " )";
9261  return description;
9262  }
9263 
9264  friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatchAnyOf&& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) {
9265  lhs.m_matchers.push_back(&rhs);
9266  return std::move(lhs);
9267  }
9268  friend MatchAnyOf operator|| (MatcherBase<ArgT> const& lhs, MatchAnyOf&& rhs) {
9269  rhs.m_matchers.insert(rhs.m_matchers.begin(), &lhs);
9270  return std::move(rhs);
9271  }
9272 
9273  private:
9274  std::vector<MatcherBase<ArgT> const*> m_matchers;
9275  };

9279  template<typename ArgT>
9280  MatchAnyOf<ArgT> operator|| (MatchAnyOf<ArgT> const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgT> const& rhs) = delete;

9285 
9286  template<typename ArgT>
9287  struct MatchNotOf final : MatcherBase<ArgT> {
9288 
9289  explicit MatchNotOf( MatcherBase<ArgT> const& underlyingMatcher ):
9290  m_underlyingMatcher( underlyingMatcher )
9291  {}
9292 
9293  bool match( ArgT const& arg ) const override {
9294  return !m_underlyingMatcher.match( arg );
9295  }
9296 
9297  std::string describe() const override {
9298  return "not " + m_underlyingMatcher.toString();
9299  }
9300 
9301  private:
9302  MatcherBase<ArgT> const& m_underlyingMatcher;
9303  };

9305  } // namespace Detail

9307  template <typename T>
9308  Detail::MatchAllOf<T> operator&& (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
9309  return Detail::MatchAllOf<T>{} && lhs && rhs;
9310  }
9311  template <typename T>
9312  Detail::MatchAnyOf<T> operator|| (MatcherBase<T> const& lhs, MatcherBase<T> const& rhs) {
9313  return Detail::MatchAnyOf<T>{} || lhs || rhs;
9314  }
9315 
9316  template <typename T>
9317  Detail::MatchNotOf<T> operator! (MatcherBase<T> const& matcher) {
9318  return Detail::MatchNotOf<T>{ matcher };
9319  }

9391  struct MatcherGenericBase : MatcherUntypedBase {
9392  MatcherGenericBase() = default;
9393  virtual ~MatcherGenericBase(); // = default;

9396  MatcherGenericBase(MatcherGenericBase&&) = default;

9403  namespace Detail {
9404  template<std::size_t N, std::size_t M>
9405  std::array<void const*, N + M> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, std::array<void const*, M> && rhs) {
9406  std::array<void const*, N + M> arr{};
9407  std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
9408  std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), M, arr.begin() + N);
9409  return arr;
9410  }
9411 
9412  template<std::size_t N>
9413  std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(std::array<void const*, N> && lhs, void const* rhs) {
9414  std::array<void const*, N+1> arr{};
9415  std::copy_n(lhs.begin(), N, arr.begin());
9416  arr[N] = rhs;
9417  return arr;
9418  }
9419 
9420  template<std::size_t N>
9421  std::array<void const*, N+1> array_cat(void const* lhs, std::array<void const*, N> && rhs) {
9422  std::array<void const*, N + 1> arr{ {lhs} };
9423  std::copy_n(rhs.begin(), N, arr.begin() + 1);
9424  return arr;
9425  }

9431  #else // CATCH_CPP17_OR_GREATER

9433  template<typename... Cond>
9434  struct conjunction : std::true_type {};
9435 
9436  template<typename Cond, typename... Rest>
9437  struct conjunction<Cond, Rest...> : std::integral_constant<bool, Cond::value && conjunction<Rest...>::value> {};
9438 
9439  #endif // CATCH_CPP17_OR_GREATER

9441  template<typename T>
9442  using is_generic_matcher = std::is_base_of<
9443  Catch::Matchers::MatcherGenericBase,
9444  std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
9445  >;
9446 
9447  template<typename... Ts>
9448  using are_generic_matchers = conjunction<is_generic_matcher<Ts>...>;
9449 
9450  template<typename T>
9451  using is_matcher = std::is_base_of<
9452  Catch::Matchers::MatcherUntypedBase,
9453  std::remove_cv_t<std::remove_reference_t<T>>
9454  >;

9457  template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
9458  bool match_all_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
9459  return true;
9460  }
9461 
9462  template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
9463  bool match_all_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
9464  return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) && match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
9465  }
9466 
9467 
9468  template<std::size_t N, typename Arg>
9469  bool match_any_of(Arg&&, std::array<void const*, N> const&, std::index_sequence<>) {
9470  return false;
9471  }
9472 
9473  template<typename T, typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t N, typename Arg, std::size_t Idx, std::size_t... Indices>
9474  bool match_any_of(Arg&& arg, std::array<void const*, N> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx, Indices...>) {
9475  return static_cast<T const*>(matchers[Idx])->match(arg) || match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, matchers, std::index_sequence<Indices...>{});
9476  }
9477 
9478  std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::string const* descriptions_begin, std::string const* descriptions_end);
9479 
9480  template<typename... MatcherTs, std::size_t... Idx>
9481  std::string describe_multi_matcher(StringRef combine, std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> const& matchers, std::index_sequence<Idx...>) {
9482  std::array<std::string, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> descriptions {{
9483  static_cast<MatcherTs const*>(matchers[Idx])->toString()...
9484  }};
9485 
9486  return describe_multi_matcher(combine, descriptions.data(), descriptions.data() + descriptions.size());
9487  }

9490  template<typename... MatcherTs>
9491  struct MatchAllOfGeneric final : MatcherGenericBase {
9492  MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9493  MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9494  MatchAllOfGeneric(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
9495  MatchAllOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAllOfGeneric&&) = default;
9496 
9497  MatchAllOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
9498  explicit MatchAllOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
9499 
9500  template<typename Arg>
9501  bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
9502  return match_all_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
9503  }
9504 
9505  std::string describe() const override {
9506  return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" and "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
9507  }
9508 
9509  std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> m_matchers;
9510 
9512  template<typename... MatchersRHS>
9513  friend
9514  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator && (
9515  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
9516  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
9517  return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(std::move(lhs.m_matchers), std::move(rhs.m_matchers))};
9518  }
9519 
9521  template<typename MatcherRHS>
9522  friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value,
9523  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator && (
9524  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
9525  MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
9526  return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(std::move(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(&rhs))};
9527  }
9528 
9530  template<typename MatcherLHS>
9531  friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value,
9532  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator && (
9533  MatcherLHS const& lhs,
9534  MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
9535  return MatchAllOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), std::move(rhs.m_matchers))};
9536  }
9537  };
9538

9540  template<typename... MatcherTs>
9541  struct MatchAnyOfGeneric final : MatcherGenericBase {
9542  MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9543  MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9544  MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
9545  MatchAnyOfGeneric& operator=(MatchAnyOfGeneric&&) = default;
9546 
9547  MatchAnyOfGeneric(MatcherTs const&... matchers) : m_matchers{ {std::addressof(matchers)...} } {}
9548  explicit MatchAnyOfGeneric(std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> matchers) : m_matchers{matchers} {}
9549 
9550  template<typename Arg>
9551  bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
9552  return match_any_of<MatcherTs...>(arg, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
9553  }
9554 
9555  std::string describe() const override {
9556  return describe_multi_matcher<MatcherTs...>(" or "_sr, m_matchers, std::index_sequence_for<MatcherTs...>{});
9557  }
9558 
9559  std::array<void const*, sizeof...(MatcherTs)> m_matchers;
9560 
9562  template<typename... MatchersRHS>
9563  friend MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...> operator || (
9564  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
9565  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatchersRHS...>&& rhs) {
9566  return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatchersRHS...>{array_cat(std::move(lhs.m_matchers), std::move(rhs.m_matchers))};
9567  }
9568 
9570  template<typename MatcherRHS>
9571  friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherRHS>::value,
9572  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>> operator || (
9573  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& lhs,
9574  MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
9575  return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs..., MatcherRHS>{array_cat(std::move(lhs.m_matchers), static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(rhs)))};
9576  }
9577 
9579  template<typename MatcherLHS>
9580  friend std::enable_if_t<is_matcher<MatcherLHS>::value,
9581  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>> operator || (
9582  MatcherLHS const& lhs,
9583  MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherTs...>&& rhs) {
9584  return MatchAnyOfGeneric<MatcherLHS, MatcherTs...>{array_cat(static_cast<void const*>(std::addressof(lhs)), std::move(rhs.m_matchers))};
9585  }

9589  template<typename MatcherT>
9590  struct MatchNotOfGeneric final : MatcherGenericBase {
9591  MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9592  MatchNotOfGeneric& operator=(MatchNotOfGeneric const&) = delete;
9593  MatchNotOfGeneric(MatchNotOfGeneric&&) = default;
9594  MatchNotOfGeneric& operator=(MatchNotOfGeneric&&) = default;
9595 
9596  explicit MatchNotOfGeneric(MatcherT const& matcher) : m_matcher{matcher} {}
9597 
9598  template<typename Arg>
9599  bool match(Arg&& arg) const {
9600  return !m_matcher.match(arg);
9601  }
9602 
9603  std::string describe() const override {
9604  return "not " + m_matcher.toString();
9605  }
9606 
9608  friend MatcherT const& operator ! (MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT> const& matcher) {
9609  return matcher.m_matcher;
9610  }
9611  private:
9612  MatcherT const& m_matcher;
9613  };

9620  operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
9621  return { lhs, rhs };
9622  }

9626  operator || (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherRHS const& rhs) {
9627  return { lhs, rhs };
9628  }

9633  operator ! (MatcherT const& matcher) {
9634  return Detail::MatchNotOfGeneric<MatcherT>{matcher};
9635  }

9641  operator && (MatcherLHS const& lhs, MatcherBase<ArgRHS> const& rhs) {

9755 namespace Catch {
9756  namespace Matchers {
9758  template <typename T, typename Equality>
9759  class ContainsElementMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
9760  T m_desired;
9761  Equality m_eq;
9762  public:
9763  template <typename T2, typename Equality2>
9764  ContainsElementMatcher(T2&& target, Equality2&& predicate):
9765  m_desired(std::forward<T2>(target)),
9766  m_eq(std::forward<Equality2>(predicate))
9767  {}
9768 
9769  std::string describe() const override {
9770  return "contains element " + Catch::Detail::stringify(m_desired);
9771  }
9772 
9773  template <typename RangeLike>
9774  bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
9775  using std::begin; using std::end;
9776 
9777  return end(rng) != std::find_if(begin(rng), end(rng),
9778  [&](auto const& elem) {
9779  return m_eq(elem, m_desired);
9780  });
9781  }
9782  };
9783 
9785  template <typename Matcher>
9786  class ContainsMatcherMatcher final : public MatcherGenericBase {
9787  Matcher m_matcher;
9788  public:
9789  // Note that we do a copy+move to avoid having to SFINAE this
9790  // constructor (and also avoid some perfect forwarding failure
9791  // cases)
9792  ContainsMatcherMatcher(Matcher matcher):
9793  m_matcher(std::move(matcher))
9794  {}
9795 
9796  template <typename RangeLike>
9797  bool match(RangeLike&& rng) const {
9798  using std::begin; using std::endl;
9799  for (auto&& elem : rng) {
9800  if (m_matcher.match(elem)) {
9801  return true;
9802  }
9803  }
9804  return false;
9805  }
9806 
9807  std::string describe() const override {
9808  return "contains element matching " + m_matcher.describe();
9809  }
9810  };
9811 
9817  template <typename T>
9818  std::enable_if_t<!Detail::is_matcher<T>::value,
9819  ContainsElementMatcher<T, std::equal_to<>>> Contains(T&& elem) {
9820  return { std::forward<T>(elem), std::equal_to<>{} };
9821  }
9822 
9824  template <typename Matcher>
9825  std::enable_if_t<Detail::is_matcher<Matcher>::value,
9826  ContainsMatcherMatcher<Matcher>> Contains(Matcher&& matcher) {
9827  return { std::forward<Matcher>(matcher) };
9828  }
9829 
9835  template <typename T, typename Equality>
9836  ContainsElementMatcher<T, Equality> Contains(T&& elem, Equality&& eq) {
9837  return { std::forward<T>(elem), std::forward<Equality>(eq) };
9838  }
9839 
9840  }

9897  bool match(double const& matchee) const override;

9899  private:
9900  double m_target;
9901  uint64_t m_ulps;
9902  Detail::FloatingPointKind m_type;
9903  };
9904 
9905  // Given IEEE-754 format for floats and doubles, we can assume
9906  // that float -> double promotion is lossless. Given this, we can
9907  // assume that if we do the standard relative comparison of
9908  // |lhs - rhs| <= epsilon * max(fabs(lhs), fabs(rhs)), then we get
9909  // the same result if we do this for floats, as if we do this for
9910  // doubles that were promoted from floats.
9911  struct WithinRelMatcher final : MatcherBase<double> {
9912  WithinRelMatcher(double target, double epsilon);
9913  bool match(double const& matchee) const override;
9914  std::string describe() const override;
9915  private:
9916  double m_target;
9917  double m_epsilon;
9918  };
9919 
9921  WithinUlpsMatcher WithinULP(double target, uint64_t maxUlpDiff);
9923  WithinUlpsMatcher WithinULP(float target, uint64_t maxUlpDiff);
9925  WithinAbsMatcher WithinAbs(double target, double margin);
9926 
9928  WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target, double eps);
9930  WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(double target);
9932  WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target, float eps);
9934  WithinRelMatcher WithinRel(float target);
9935 
9936 } // namespace Matchers
9937 } // namespace Catch
9938 
9939 #endif // CATCH_MATCHERS_FLOATING_HPP_INCLUDED

9956 template <typename T, typename Predicate>
9957 class PredicateMatcher final : public MatcherBase<T> {
9958  Predicate m_predicate;
9959  std::string m_description;
9960 public:
9961 
9962  PredicateMatcher(Predicate&& elem, std::string const& descr)
9963  :m_predicate(std::forward<Predicate>(elem)),
9964  m_description(Detail::finalizeDescription(descr))
9965  {}
9966 
9967  bool match( T const& item ) const override {
9968  return m_predicate(item);
9969  }
9970 
9971  std::string describe() const override {
9972  return m_description;
9973  }
9974 };
9975 
9981  template<typename T, typename Pred>
9982  PredicateMatcher<T, Pred> Predicate(Pred&& predicate, std::string const& description = "") {
9983  static_assert(is_callable<Pred(T)>::value, "Predicate not callable with argument T");
9984  static_assert(std::is_same<bool, FunctionReturnType<Pred, T>>::value, "Predicate does not return bool");
9985  return PredicateMatcher<T, Pred>(std::forward<Pred>(predicate), description);
9986  }

10073  template<typename T, typename Alloc>
10074  struct VectorContainsElementMatcher final : MatcherBase<std::vector<T, Alloc>> {
10075 
10076  VectorContainsElementMatcher(T const& comparator):
10077  m_comparator(comparator)
10078  {}
10079 
10080  bool match(std::vector<T, Alloc> const& v) const override {
10081  for (auto const& el : v) {
10082  if (el == m_comparator) {
10083  return true;
10084  }
10085  }
10086  return false;
10087  }
10088 
10089  std::string describe() const override {
10090  return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
10091  }
10092 
10093  T const& m_comparator;
10094  };
10095 
10096  template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
10097  struct ContainsMatcher final : MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
10098 
10099  ContainsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
10100  m_comparator( comparator )
10101  {}
10102 
10103  bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
10104  // !TBD: see note in EqualsMatcher
10105  if (m_comparator.size() > v.size())
10106  return false;
10107  for (auto const& comparator : m_comparator) {
10108  auto present = false;
10109  for (const auto& el : v) {
10110  if (el == comparator) {
10111  present = true;
10112  break;
10113  }
10114  }
10115  if (!present) {
10116  return false;
10117  }
10118  }
10119  return true;
10120  }
10121  std::string describe() const override {
10122  return "Contains: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
10123  }
10124 
10125  std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
10126  };
10127 
10128  template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
10129  struct EqualsMatcher final : MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
10130 
10131  EqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
10132  m_comparator( comparator )
10133  {}
10134 
10135  bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
10136  // !TBD: This currently works if all elements can be compared using !=
10137  // - a more general approach would be via a compare template that defaults
10138  // to using !=. but could be specialised for, e.g. std::vector<T> etc
10139  // - then just call that directly
10140  if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
10141  return false;
10142  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
10143  if (m_comparator[i] != v[i])
10144  return false;
10145  return true;
10146  }
10147  std::string describe() const override {
10148  return "Equals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
10149  }
10150  std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
10151  };
10152 
10153  template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
10154  struct ApproxMatcher final : MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
10155 
10156  ApproxMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& comparator):
10157  m_comparator( comparator )
10158  {}
10159 
10160  bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& v) const override {
10161  if (m_comparator.size() != v.size())
10162  return false;
10163  for (std::size_t i = 0; i < v.size(); ++i)
10164  if (m_comparator[i] != approx(v[i]))
10165  return false;
10166  return true;
10167  }
10168  std::string describe() const override {
10169  return "is approx: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify( m_comparator );
10170  }
10171  template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
10172  ApproxMatcher& epsilon( T const& newEpsilon ) {
10173  approx.epsilon(static_cast<double>(newEpsilon));
10174  return *this;
10175  }
10176  template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
10177  ApproxMatcher& margin( T const& newMargin ) {
10178  approx.margin(static_cast<double>(newMargin));
10179  return *this;
10180  }
10181  template <typename = std::enable_if_t<std::is_constructible<double, T>::value>>
10182  ApproxMatcher& scale( T const& newScale ) {
10183  approx.scale(static_cast<double>(newScale));
10184  return *this;
10185  }
10186 
10187  std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_comparator;
10188  mutable Catch::Approx approx = Catch::Approx::custom();
10189  };
10190 
10191  template<typename T, typename AllocComp, typename AllocMatch>
10192  struct UnorderedEqualsMatcher final : MatcherBase<std::vector<T, AllocMatch>> {
10193  UnorderedEqualsMatcher(std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& target):
10194  m_target(target)
10195  {}
10196  bool match(std::vector<T, AllocMatch> const& vec) const override {
10197  if (m_target.size() != vec.size()) {
10198  return false;
10199  }
10200  return std::is_permutation(m_target.begin(), m_target.end(), vec.begin());
10201  }
10202 
10203  std::string describe() const override {
10204  return "UnorderedEquals: " + ::Catch::Detail::stringify(m_target);
10205  }
10206  private:
10207  std::vector<T, AllocComp> const& m_target;
10208  };

10287  template<typename T>
10288  struct LazyStat : Option<T> {
10289  LazyStat& operator=(T const& _value) {
10290  Option<T>::operator=(_value);
10291  used = false;
10292  return *this;
10293  }
10294  void reset() {
10295  Option<T>::reset();
10296  used = false;
10297  }
10298  bool used = false;

10336  // Don't do anything with this by default.
10337  // It can optionally be overridden in the derived class.
10338  }
10339 
10340  IConfig const* m_config;

10344  LazyStat<GroupInfo> currentGroupInfo;

10508  struct CumulativeReporterBase : IStreamingReporter {
10509  template<typename T, typename ChildNodeT>
10510  struct Node {
10511  explicit Node( T const& _value ) : value( _value ) {}
10512  virtual ~Node() {}
10513 
10514  using ChildNodes = std::vector<std::shared_ptr<ChildNodeT>>;
10515  T value;
10516  ChildNodes children;
10517  };
10518  struct SectionNode {
10519  explicit SectionNode(SectionStats const& _stats) : stats(_stats) {}
10520 
10521  bool operator == (SectionNode const& other) const {
10522  return stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo == other.stats.sectionInfo.lineInfo;
10523  }
10524 
10525  SectionStats stats;
10526  using ChildSections = std::vector<std::shared_ptr<SectionNode>>;
10527  using Assertions = std::vector<AssertionStats>;
10528  ChildSections childSections;
10529  Assertions assertions;
10530  std::string stdOut;
10531  std::string stdErr;
10532  };
10533 
10534 
10535  using TestCaseNode = Node<TestCaseStats, SectionNode>;
10536  using TestGroupNode = Node<TestGroupStats, TestCaseNode>;
10537  using TestRunNode = Node<TestRunStats, TestGroupNode>;
10538 
10539  CumulativeReporterBase( ReporterConfig const& _config ):
10540  m_config( _config.fullConfig() ), stream( _config.stream() ) {}
10541  ~CumulativeReporterBase() override;
10542 
10543  void testRunStarting( TestRunInfo const& ) override {}
10544  void testGroupStarting( GroupInfo const& ) override {}
10545 
10546  void testCaseStarting( TestCaseInfo const& ) override {}
10547 
10548  void sectionStarting( SectionInfo const& sectionInfo ) override;
10549 
10550  void assertionStarting( AssertionInfo const& ) override {}
10551 
10552  bool assertionEnded( AssertionStats const& assertionStats ) override;
10553  void sectionEnded( SectionStats const& sectionStats ) override;
10554  void testCaseEnded( TestCaseStats const& testCaseStats ) override;
10555  void testGroupEnded( TestGroupStats const& testGroupStats ) override;
10556  void testRunEnded( TestRunStats const& testRunStats ) override;
10557  virtual void testRunEndedCumulative() = 0;
10558 
10559  void skipTest(TestCaseInfo const&) override {}
10560 
10561  IConfig const* m_config;
10562  std::ostream& stream;
10563  std::vector<AssertionStats> m_assertions;
10564  std::vector<std::vector<std::shared_ptr<SectionNode>>> m_sections;
10565  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<TestCaseNode>> m_testCases;
10566  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<TestGroupNode>> m_testGroups;
10567 
10568  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<TestRunNode>> m_testRuns;
10569 
10570  std::shared_ptr<SectionNode> m_rootSection;
10571  std::shared_ptr<SectionNode> m_deepestSection;
10572  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<SectionNode>> m_sectionStack;
10573  };
